WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.491 align:middle line:90%


00:00:01.491 --> 00:00:03.479 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:03.479 --> 00:01:06.330 align:middle line:90%


00:01:06.330 --> 00:01:07.630 align:middle line:84%
FREDRICK (VOICEOVER):
What would happen

00:01:07.630 --> 00:01:11.610 align:middle line:84%
if you had the chance to go
back in time and heal the past?

00:01:11.610 --> 00:01:13.730 align:middle line:84%
And maybe even say
some of the things

00:01:13.730 --> 00:01:16.490 align:middle line:84%
you never had the courage
to say to the person

00:01:16.490 --> 00:01:18.620 align:middle line:90%
who meant the most to you?

00:01:18.620 --> 00:01:20.940 align:middle line:90%
Does it make sense to even try?

00:01:20.940 --> 00:01:23.060 align:middle line:84%
Or is it better to
let it lie there,

00:01:23.060 --> 00:01:25.100 align:middle line:84%
like a memory in the
back of your mind

00:01:25.100 --> 00:01:28.100 align:middle line:90%
that never seems to fade?

00:01:28.100 --> 00:01:31.520 align:middle line:84%
But what would you say if that
person was suddenly right there

00:01:31.520 --> 00:01:34.870 align:middle line:84%
in front of you, after
years of separation,

00:01:34.870 --> 00:01:37.080 align:middle line:84%
and you're able to see
deeper into their eyes

00:01:37.080 --> 00:01:41.950 align:middle line:84%
than ever before, maybe all
the way to your own heart?

00:01:41.950 --> 00:01:43.410 align:middle line:84%
Would it make any
difference at all?

00:01:43.410 --> 00:01:47.860 align:middle line:84%
Or would it just tear open
the wound one last time,

00:01:47.860 --> 00:01:50.450 align:middle line:90%
just for old time's sake?

00:01:50.450 --> 00:01:52.410 align:middle line:84%
Maybe it's best to
learn from your mistakes

00:01:52.410 --> 00:01:55.710 align:middle line:84%
and become cynical, like
a war veteran who flinches

00:01:55.710 --> 00:01:58.380 align:middle line:90%
every time they hear a gunshot.

00:01:58.380 --> 00:02:01.350 align:middle line:84%
But what if they weren't
mistakes at all, but the fire

00:02:01.350 --> 00:02:03.890 align:middle line:90%
that tempers the steel?

00:02:03.890 --> 00:02:06.488 align:middle line:84%
Well, there's only
one way to find out.

00:02:06.488 --> 00:02:14.800 align:middle line:90%


00:02:14.800 --> 00:02:17.728 align:middle line:90%
KATHERINE: Anticipation's over.

00:02:17.728 --> 00:02:19.636 align:middle line:90%
Catherine.

00:02:19.636 --> 00:02:21.550 align:middle line:90%
Wow.

00:02:21.550 --> 00:02:22.700 align:middle line:90%
You're here.

00:02:22.700 --> 00:02:23.610 align:middle line:90%
I'm here.

00:02:23.610 --> 00:02:24.850 align:middle line:90%
Strange, but true.

00:02:24.850 --> 00:02:39.390 align:middle line:90%


00:02:39.390 --> 00:02:40.630 align:middle line:90%
FREDRICK: You look great.

00:02:40.630 --> 00:02:42.610 align:middle line:90%
Hardly changed at all.

00:02:42.610 --> 00:02:43.840 align:middle line:84%
Don't begin with
a lie, Fredrick.

00:02:43.840 --> 00:02:44.770 align:middle line:90%
We've both changed.

00:02:44.770 --> 00:02:46.300 align:middle line:90%
Six years'll do that to you.

00:02:46.300 --> 00:02:48.560 align:middle line:84%
FREDRICK: -More
mature, that all.

00:02:48.560 --> 00:02:50.580 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise, you're exactly
the same as I remember.

00:02:50.580 --> 00:02:52.050 align:middle line:90%
You look better.

00:02:52.050 --> 00:02:54.380 align:middle line:84%
Same face, but soft
around the eyes.

00:02:54.380 --> 00:02:55.700 align:middle line:90%
Softer?

00:02:55.700 --> 00:02:56.837 align:middle line:90%
That's surprising.

00:02:56.837 --> 00:02:57.970 align:middle line:84%
I would have thought
the opposite.

00:02:57.970 --> 00:03:00.270 align:middle line:84%
Well, I'll reserve judgment
for later when I find out more

00:03:00.270 --> 00:03:01.620 align:middle line:90%
about what you've been up to.

00:03:01.620 --> 00:03:02.670 align:middle line:90%
SERVER: Hi.

00:03:02.670 --> 00:03:04.145 align:middle line:84%
Could I get you folks
something to drink?

00:03:04.145 --> 00:03:06.510 align:middle line:90%
I'd like an americano, please.

00:03:06.510 --> 00:03:08.109 align:middle line:84%
Can I have a minute?
SERVER: Sure.

00:03:08.109 --> 00:03:13.230 align:middle line:90%


00:03:13.230 --> 00:03:14.715 align:middle line:84%
I'll have the same
thing he's having.

00:03:14.715 --> 00:03:15.750 align:middle line:90%
Hang on a second.

00:03:15.750 --> 00:03:16.720 align:middle line:90%
What?

00:03:16.720 --> 00:03:18.696 align:middle line:90%
Some things never change.

00:03:18.696 --> 00:03:20.330 align:middle line:84%
If I had ordered
a cappuccino, you

00:03:20.330 --> 00:03:22.200 align:middle line:84%
would have ordered a cappuccino,
but not after looking

00:03:22.200 --> 00:03:24.560 align:middle line:90%
at the whole menu first.

00:03:24.560 --> 00:03:26.135 align:middle line:84%
That's what you
remember about me?

00:03:26.135 --> 00:03:28.220 align:middle line:10%
And it's not even true.

00:03:28.220 --> 00:03:31.295 align:middle line:84%
Can I change my order
to a mocha, please?

00:03:31.295 --> 00:03:33.774 align:middle line:90%
SERVER: Of course, ma'am.

00:03:33.774 --> 00:03:36.180 align:middle line:90%
Thanks.

00:03:36.180 --> 00:03:38.430 align:middle line:90%
So the dies have been cast.

00:03:38.430 --> 00:03:43.570 align:middle line:84%
And it feels like days have
gone by instead of years.

00:03:43.570 --> 00:03:45.750 align:middle line:84%
Makes you wonder if
it's even worth it.

00:03:45.750 --> 00:03:49.170 align:middle line:84%
I mean, who's to say you
didn't make the exact decision

00:03:49.170 --> 00:03:50.660 align:middle line:84%
that you were
supposed to back then

00:03:50.660 --> 00:03:52.920 align:middle line:84%
and everything
turned out exactly

00:03:52.920 --> 00:03:55.420 align:middle line:90%
the way it was supposed to?

00:03:55.420 --> 00:04:00.330 align:middle line:84%
Why do we idealize what we lost,
as if we left ourselves behind

00:04:00.330 --> 00:04:01.460 align:middle line:84%
and we're never
going to be happy

00:04:01.460 --> 00:04:03.708 align:middle line:90%
again unless we get it back?

00:04:03.708 --> 00:04:07.400 align:middle line:84%
The funny is that if he
was the one that left her,

00:04:07.400 --> 00:04:09.690 align:middle line:84%
everything would be
reversed, and she'd be

00:04:09.690 --> 00:04:13.320 align:middle line:90%
the one all screwed up inside.

00:04:13.320 --> 00:04:15.330 align:middle line:84%
On the other hand, she
has her own dilemma.

00:04:15.330 --> 00:04:17.920 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes, there's a
part of us that wonders

00:04:17.920 --> 00:04:19.100 align:middle line:90%
if we made the right choice.

00:04:19.100 --> 00:04:22.810 align:middle line:84%
And we go into a situation
hoping the other person's

00:04:22.810 --> 00:04:26.320 align:middle line:90%
more lost than we are.

00:04:26.320 --> 00:04:28.040 align:middle line:90%
What if they're not?

00:04:28.040 --> 00:04:30.860 align:middle line:84%
It'd really suck if you got
back together years later

00:04:30.860 --> 00:04:34.860 align:middle line:84%
and you were the one with
the bags under your eyes.

00:04:34.860 --> 00:04:38.620 align:middle line:84%
My advice is that if
you have to do this,

00:04:38.620 --> 00:04:41.900 align:middle line:84%
you get it over with
as quick as you can.

00:04:41.900 --> 00:04:44.000 align:middle line:84%
Past is gone, and
there's nothing

00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:47.595 align:middle line:90%
you can do to get time back.

00:04:47.595 --> 00:04:51.400 align:middle line:84%
You know, on the other hand,
the heart has a logic the mind

00:04:51.400 --> 00:04:53.570 align:middle line:90%
is never going to understand.

00:04:53.570 --> 00:04:55.680 align:middle line:90%
So why even try?

00:04:55.680 --> 00:04:58.760 align:middle line:84%
May as well just
get on with living.

00:04:58.760 --> 00:05:01.720 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: I was glad to
hear that you're married.

00:05:01.720 --> 00:05:03.220 align:middle line:90%
Susan, right?

00:05:03.220 --> 00:05:04.619 align:middle line:84%
Yeah.
Yeah.

00:05:04.619 --> 00:05:05.400 align:middle line:90%
She's really great.

00:05:05.400 --> 00:05:07.675 align:middle line:84%
She understood that I
needed to do this on my own.

00:05:07.675 --> 00:05:09.280 align:middle line:84%
You make it sound
like heart surgery.

00:05:09.280 --> 00:05:11.245 align:middle line:90%
I hope it's not that difficult.

00:05:11.245 --> 00:05:13.450 align:middle line:90%
Just strange, the whole thing.

00:05:13.450 --> 00:05:15.160 align:middle line:90%
I never thought it would happen.

00:05:15.160 --> 00:05:16.140 align:middle line:90%
Especially here.

00:05:16.140 --> 00:05:17.870 align:middle line:90%
Planet Ashland.

00:05:17.870 --> 00:05:19.120 align:middle line:90%
Hasn't changed much, has it?

00:05:19.120 --> 00:05:20.365 align:middle line:90%
It's grown, though.

00:05:20.365 --> 00:05:22.500 align:middle line:90%
It had to happen.

00:05:22.500 --> 00:05:24.480 align:middle line:84%
It was an undiscovered
Shangri-La for so long,

00:05:24.480 --> 00:05:27.720 align:middle line:84%
and then California
realized we were here.

00:05:27.720 --> 00:05:31.167 align:middle line:90%
I liked it better before.

00:05:31.167 --> 00:05:32.600 align:middle line:84%
I used to tell people
it was a great place

00:05:32.600 --> 00:05:34.660 align:middle line:84%
to live except for all
the hurricanes and floods.

00:05:34.660 --> 00:05:37.446 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't look like it worked.

00:05:37.446 --> 00:05:40.870 align:middle line:84%
Well, you didn't waste
much time getting out.

00:05:40.870 --> 00:05:42.738 align:middle line:90%
Let's not go there.

00:05:42.738 --> 00:05:44.200 align:middle line:90%
FREDRICK: OK.

00:05:44.200 --> 00:05:45.809 align:middle line:84%
Where do you want to go?
-I don't know.

00:05:45.809 --> 00:05:47.980 align:middle line:84%
Just being here
feels like a step.

00:05:47.980 --> 00:05:49.230 align:middle line:90%
A big step.

00:05:49.230 --> 00:05:50.870 align:middle line:90%
Maybe even catastrophic.

00:05:50.870 --> 00:05:54.280 align:middle line:90%
SERVER: Here you go.

00:05:54.280 --> 00:05:56.491 align:middle line:84%
All right.
OK.

00:05:56.491 --> 00:05:57.190 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:05:57.190 --> 00:06:01.850 align:middle line:90%


00:06:01.850 --> 00:06:04.170 align:middle line:90%
Were you nervous?

00:06:04.170 --> 00:06:07.300 align:middle line:84%
I'm actually surprised at
how comfortable it feels.

00:06:07.300 --> 00:06:09.130 align:middle line:84%
I wasn't sure, especially
sitting here waiting.

00:06:09.130 --> 00:06:10.000 align:middle line:90%
How about you?

00:06:10.000 --> 00:06:11.920 align:middle line:84%
You're not even
a little nervous?

00:06:11.920 --> 00:06:14.310 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't call
it nerves, exactly.

00:06:14.310 --> 00:06:17.950 align:middle line:84%
More like a horse in
the starting gate.

00:06:17.950 --> 00:06:21.250 align:middle line:84%
I saw you, and I felt my
heart rate increase a little,

00:06:21.250 --> 00:06:22.731 align:middle line:84%
and I just wanted
to get it over with.

00:06:22.731 --> 00:06:24.660 align:middle line:84%
FREDRICK: Great.
Could we get the check, please?

00:06:24.660 --> 00:06:27.310 align:middle line:90%
That's not what I meant.

00:06:27.310 --> 00:06:30.700 align:middle line:84%
I meant the slow
approach, you know?

00:06:30.700 --> 00:06:32.560 align:middle line:84%
Seeing you sitting
there looking around

00:06:32.560 --> 00:06:37.510 align:middle line:84%
and me wondering what I'd say
if you didn't speak first.

00:06:37.510 --> 00:06:38.960 align:middle line:90%
Anticipation's over.

00:06:38.960 --> 00:06:40.940 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:06:40.940 --> 00:06:42.700 align:middle line:84%
Not the best opening
line, but it worked.

00:06:42.700 --> 00:06:44.460 align:middle line:90%
Let's think of a better one.

00:06:44.460 --> 00:06:46.000 align:middle line:90%
A better opening line?

00:06:46.000 --> 00:06:47.040 align:middle line:90%
Why not?

00:06:47.040 --> 00:06:49.016 align:middle line:84%
We might as well make
the moment memorable.

00:06:49.016 --> 00:06:50.880 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:06:50.880 --> 00:06:57.850 align:middle line:90%
How about hello, Fredrick.

00:06:57.850 --> 00:07:00.670 align:middle line:84%
It's nice to see that the
years have treated you well.

00:07:00.670 --> 00:07:02.920 align:middle line:84%
I wish I could say the same
for you, dear Catherine.

00:07:02.920 --> 00:07:04.200 align:middle line:84%
But those years in
the cotton fields

00:07:04.200 --> 00:07:06.640 align:middle line:90%
are bound to take their toll.

00:07:06.640 --> 00:07:08.790 align:middle line:84%
And I thought 20
years of heroin abuse

00:07:08.790 --> 00:07:10.222 align:middle line:90%
would make you look thin.

00:07:10.222 --> 00:07:11.590 align:middle line:84%
High carb diet
took care of that.

00:07:11.590 --> 00:07:17.590 align:middle line:90%


00:07:17.590 --> 00:07:19.620 align:middle line:90%
So Susan couldn't come.

00:07:19.620 --> 00:07:21.980 align:middle line:90%
Tell me more about her.

00:07:21.980 --> 00:07:24.020 align:middle line:84%
We've been married
for about a year

00:07:24.020 --> 00:07:26.210 align:middle line:90%
now, together for almost three.

00:07:26.210 --> 00:07:28.761 align:middle line:90%
She's really amazing.

00:07:28.761 --> 00:07:30.870 align:middle line:84%
Of course, I wonder if
I really deserve her.

00:07:30.870 --> 00:07:32.260 align:middle line:90%
You do.

00:07:32.260 --> 00:07:33.741 align:middle line:90%
FREDRICK: Why do you say that?

00:07:33.741 --> 00:07:35.730 align:middle line:84%
Just because I haven't
seen you in six years

00:07:35.730 --> 00:07:37.905 align:middle line:84%
doesn't mean I don't
know what you deserve.

00:07:37.905 --> 00:07:38.895 align:middle line:90%
That's funny.

00:07:38.895 --> 00:07:42.309 align:middle line:90%


00:07:42.309 --> 00:07:43.008 align:middle line:90%
KATHERINE: Why?

00:07:43.008 --> 00:07:45.560 align:middle line:84%
Well, I never really
got the feeling

00:07:45.560 --> 00:07:46.640 align:middle line:90%
like I deserved you either.

00:07:46.640 --> 00:07:50.670 align:middle line:84%
And I kinda got the impression
that you agreed with me.

00:07:50.670 --> 00:07:52.900 align:middle line:90%
That's what you thought?

00:07:52.900 --> 00:07:54.950 align:middle line:84%
If I recall, that's the
way it felt at the time.

00:07:54.950 --> 00:07:56.870 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't really matter.

00:07:56.870 --> 00:07:58.280 align:middle line:90%
Obviously, you let it go.

00:07:58.280 --> 00:08:01.070 align:middle line:90%
And now, you're happily married.

00:08:01.070 --> 00:08:02.160 align:middle line:90%
FREDRICK: And you?

00:08:02.160 --> 00:08:03.690 align:middle line:90%
Me what?

00:08:03.690 --> 00:08:04.770 align:middle line:90%
You're not married?

00:08:04.770 --> 00:08:06.767 align:middle line:90%
KATHERINE: No, but I am happy.

00:08:06.767 --> 00:08:08.000 align:middle line:84%
I've had a few
serious relationships.

00:08:08.000 --> 00:08:11.700 align:middle line:90%
I just never felt like stopping.

00:08:11.700 --> 00:08:14.400 align:middle line:84%
Why do you see
marriage as stopping?

00:08:14.400 --> 00:08:16.460 align:middle line:84%
There are an infinite number
of experiences out there

00:08:16.460 --> 00:08:19.320 align:middle line:84%
and a whole lot of
people to have them with.

00:08:19.320 --> 00:08:22.280 align:middle line:84%
Maybe if I found someone
who understood me,

00:08:22.280 --> 00:08:25.090 align:middle line:84%
someone who saw the
world the way I did.

00:08:25.090 --> 00:08:26.180 align:middle line:90%
But that hasn't happened.

00:08:26.180 --> 00:08:28.300 align:middle line:90%
Life has been full, though.

00:08:28.300 --> 00:08:30.840 align:middle line:90%
I'm sure it has.

00:08:30.840 --> 00:08:32.780 align:middle line:90%
Doesn't surprise me.

00:08:32.780 --> 00:08:34.169 align:middle line:90%
What?

00:08:34.169 --> 00:08:36.037 align:middle line:84%
None of what you just
said surprises me.

00:08:36.037 --> 00:08:37.270 align:middle line:84%
You've always been
that way, at least

00:08:37.270 --> 00:08:39.049 align:middle line:90%
as long as I've known you.

00:08:39.049 --> 00:08:41.210 align:middle line:84%
Settling down was
never your style,

00:08:41.210 --> 00:08:44.179 align:middle line:84%
unless it was with someone
who was exactly like you

00:08:44.179 --> 00:08:46.250 align:middle line:90%
or maybe the exact opposite.

00:08:46.250 --> 00:08:47.750 align:middle line:90%
Which is it?

00:08:47.750 --> 00:08:50.280 align:middle line:84%
Exactly the same or
the exact opposite?

00:08:50.280 --> 00:08:51.580 align:middle line:90%
Probably opposite.

00:08:51.580 --> 00:08:52.775 align:middle line:90%
KATHERINE: Why?

00:08:52.775 --> 00:08:53.875 align:middle line:84%
If it was someone
like you, that

00:08:53.875 --> 00:08:55.480 align:middle line:90%
would have been too obvious.

00:08:55.480 --> 00:08:56.850 align:middle line:90%
That's what happened to us?

00:08:56.850 --> 00:08:58.330 align:middle line:84%
You think we were
exactly the same?

00:08:58.330 --> 00:08:59.310 align:middle line:90%
That's a bit hopeful.

00:08:59.310 --> 00:09:00.040 align:middle line:90%
It's not hopeful.

00:09:00.040 --> 00:09:01.690 align:middle line:90%
It's just the way I saw it.

00:09:01.690 --> 00:09:04.280 align:middle line:90%
You thought we were soul mates.

00:09:04.280 --> 00:09:07.680 align:middle line:90%
I don't know about that stuff.

00:09:07.680 --> 00:09:10.140 align:middle line:90%
Maybe.

00:09:10.140 --> 00:09:12.510 align:middle line:84%
All I know is that if you're
not ready to look at yourself,

00:09:12.510 --> 00:09:13.710 align:middle line:84%
it's hard when
someone else reflects

00:09:13.710 --> 00:09:16.340 align:middle line:90%
everything, both good and bad.

00:09:16.340 --> 00:09:18.737 align:middle line:90%
So tell me more about Susan.

00:09:18.737 --> 00:09:20.270 align:middle line:84%
FREDRICK: You're trying
to change the subject?

00:09:20.270 --> 00:09:23.460 align:middle line:90%


00:09:23.460 --> 00:09:28.280 align:middle line:84%
My greatest fear about this
was this-- that we get together

00:09:28.280 --> 00:09:32.690 align:middle line:84%
and rehash everything that did
or didn't happen between us.

00:09:32.690 --> 00:09:35.060 align:middle line:84%
It's just so easy to look back
and regret certain things.

00:09:35.060 --> 00:09:38.080 align:middle line:90%
But what good does it do?

00:09:38.080 --> 00:09:40.310 align:middle line:90%
We can't go back to them.

00:09:40.310 --> 00:09:42.420 align:middle line:84%
All we can do is see each
other for who we are now,

00:09:42.420 --> 00:09:48.010 align:middle line:84%
and know that maybe we helped
make each other that way.

00:09:48.010 --> 00:09:50.160 align:middle line:90%
I know you changed my life.

00:09:50.160 --> 00:09:52.340 align:middle line:84%
And there were times when it
just scared the hell out of me.

00:09:52.340 --> 00:09:55.450 align:middle line:84%
And those were the things that
I had to look at the most.

00:09:55.450 --> 00:09:56.610 align:middle line:90%
And I've done that.

00:09:56.610 --> 00:09:58.700 align:middle line:84%
I've looked into all
the scary corners

00:09:58.700 --> 00:10:02.410 align:middle line:84%
and shed some light in there,
and you probably have too.

00:10:02.410 --> 00:10:03.610 align:middle line:84%
And now, maybe, we
can see something

00:10:03.610 --> 00:10:06.450 align:middle line:90%
we didn't see back then.

00:10:06.450 --> 00:10:09.120 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, the past is
gone, and I'm glad.

00:10:09.120 --> 00:10:10.490 align:middle line:84%
I think maybe we
did see it back then,

00:10:10.490 --> 00:10:13.071 align:middle line:84%
but we weren't ready
for what it meant.

00:10:13.071 --> 00:10:15.470 align:middle line:84%
Whatever.
I'm just glad you called.

00:10:15.470 --> 00:10:17.370 align:middle line:90%
How surprised were you?

00:10:17.370 --> 00:10:18.700 align:middle line:90%
Are you kidding?

00:10:18.700 --> 00:10:21.957 align:middle line:84%
I don't think I've ever
been more surprised.

00:10:21.957 --> 00:10:23.690 align:middle line:84%
I never understood why you
ended it the way you did,

00:10:23.690 --> 00:10:26.644 align:middle line:84%
but after so many years,
you just let it go.

00:10:26.644 --> 00:10:28.010 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: You probably
think I broke off

00:10:28.010 --> 00:10:29.960 align:middle line:90%
communications because of you.

00:10:29.960 --> 00:10:32.600 align:middle line:84%
Well, what else was
I supposed to think?

00:10:32.600 --> 00:10:36.050 align:middle line:84%
Did it ever occur to
you that I did it for me?

00:10:36.050 --> 00:10:37.050 align:middle line:90%
That was one of your problems.

00:10:37.050 --> 00:10:39.964 align:middle line:90%
It was always about you.

00:10:39.964 --> 00:10:41.330 align:middle line:84%
You weren't the only
one who had feelings

00:10:41.330 --> 00:10:42.420 align:middle line:90%
about what happened between us.

00:10:42.420 --> 00:10:44.105 align:middle line:84%
I had to break off
communication completely,

00:10:44.105 --> 00:10:48.030 align:middle line:84%
or else neither one of us would
have been able to move on.

00:10:48.030 --> 00:10:50.430 align:middle line:90%
It was the opposite for me.

00:10:50.430 --> 00:10:52.040 align:middle line:84%
I think the fact
that we never had

00:10:52.040 --> 00:10:54.530 align:middle line:90%
any real closure kept it alive.

00:10:54.530 --> 00:10:57.150 align:middle line:84%
If I'd been able to talk
to you-- not all the time,

00:10:57.150 --> 00:10:59.880 align:middle line:84%
but once in awhile-- it
would have been easier.

00:10:59.880 --> 00:11:03.210 align:middle line:84%
It took a whole year before
I was able to let you go.

00:11:03.210 --> 00:11:05.040 align:middle line:90%
I find that hard to believe.

00:11:05.040 --> 00:11:05.970 align:middle line:90%
Why do you say that?

00:11:05.970 --> 00:11:07.260 align:middle line:84%
You always went
through things fast.

00:11:07.260 --> 00:11:08.300 align:middle line:90%
I doubt I was any different.

00:11:08.300 --> 00:11:11.550 align:middle line:90%


00:11:11.550 --> 00:11:12.890 align:middle line:90%
How's your coffee?

00:11:12.890 --> 00:11:16.039 align:middle line:84%
Now, who's trying to
change the subject?

00:11:16.039 --> 00:11:18.005 align:middle line:84%
I just don't think you have
any ideas what I went through.

00:11:18.005 --> 00:11:21.244 align:middle line:90%


00:11:21.244 --> 00:11:22.310 align:middle line:90%
I don't think you have any idea.

00:11:22.310 --> 00:11:28.866 align:middle line:90%


00:11:28.866 --> 00:11:29.565 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:11:29.565 --> 00:11:34.730 align:middle line:90%


00:11:34.730 --> 00:11:37.460 align:middle line:90%
I'm sorry.

00:11:37.460 --> 00:11:39.080 align:middle line:84%
I'm sorry I broke
off communications.

00:11:39.080 --> 00:11:40.592 align:middle line:84%
That's one of the
things that I regret.

00:11:40.592 --> 00:11:44.000 align:middle line:90%


00:11:44.000 --> 00:11:47.032 align:middle line:84%
There are a lot of
things I regret too.

00:11:47.032 --> 00:11:49.422 align:middle line:90%
I know.

00:11:49.422 --> 00:11:53.690 align:middle line:84%
But here we are,
six years later.

00:11:53.690 --> 00:11:57.116 align:middle line:84%
So are you still working
as a war correspondent?

00:11:57.116 --> 00:12:00.040 align:middle line:84%
I'm still out there, I'm just
not doing the dangerous stuff.

00:12:00.040 --> 00:12:01.930 align:middle line:84%
I gave up the war zone
things a few years ago,

00:12:01.930 --> 00:12:03.190 align:middle line:90%
KATHERINE: I know.

00:12:03.190 --> 00:12:05.310 align:middle line:84%
I can't say that I was
disappointed to hear that.

00:12:05.310 --> 00:12:06.710 align:middle line:90%
FREDRICK: You know?

00:12:06.710 --> 00:12:08.362 align:middle line:90%
Have you been following me?

00:12:08.362 --> 00:12:11.470 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: Yeah, I check
every once in awhile.

00:12:11.470 --> 00:12:13.310 align:middle line:84%
I remember when
we were together,

00:12:13.310 --> 00:12:14.970 align:middle line:84%
you went off to
this war in Africa,

00:12:14.970 --> 00:12:17.687 align:middle line:84%
and I was sure I was never
going to see you again.

00:12:17.687 --> 00:12:19.520 align:middle line:84%
That was one of the hardest
parts about being with you.

00:12:19.520 --> 00:12:22.286 align:middle line:90%


00:12:22.286 --> 00:12:24.686 align:middle line:90%
You never let on.

00:12:24.686 --> 00:12:26.840 align:middle line:84%
It's because you didn't
see me when you were gone.

00:12:26.840 --> 00:12:28.900 align:middle line:90%
For you, it was easy.

00:12:28.900 --> 00:12:30.760 align:middle line:90%
FREDRICK: It wasn't easy.

00:12:30.760 --> 00:12:33.150 align:middle line:90%
Leaving you was never easy.

00:12:33.150 --> 00:12:35.831 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: So you'd
give it up for Susan?

00:12:35.831 --> 00:12:36.530 align:middle line:90%
I guess.

00:12:36.530 --> 00:12:39.480 align:middle line:90%


00:12:39.480 --> 00:12:42.100 align:middle line:84%
Besides, it's all about
taking risks these days.

00:12:42.100 --> 00:12:42.810 align:middle line:90%
It's too dangerous.

00:12:42.810 --> 00:12:45.480 align:middle line:90%


00:12:45.480 --> 00:12:47.210 align:middle line:90%
So what do you do now?

00:12:47.210 --> 00:12:49.570 align:middle line:84%
FREDRICK: Mostly just
local freelance stuff.

00:12:49.570 --> 00:12:53.450 align:middle line:84%
I just wrote an article about
a local grade school that

00:12:53.450 --> 00:12:55.080 align:middle line:84%
won the world's record
for making the world's

00:12:55.080 --> 00:12:56.690 align:middle line:90%
longest string of popcorn.

00:12:56.690 --> 00:12:57.470 align:middle line:90%
KATHERINE: No way.

00:12:57.470 --> 00:13:00.210 align:middle line:84%
Hey, it was picked up
by two wire services.

00:13:00.210 --> 00:13:03.370 align:middle line:84%
Besides, it keeps
me close to Susan.

00:13:03.370 --> 00:13:05.486 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: I never thought you'd
give up the wars for popcorn.

00:13:05.486 --> 00:13:08.230 align:middle line:90%
It's more like they gave me up.

00:13:08.230 --> 00:13:11.214 align:middle line:84%
When I got married, I
was done taking risks.

00:13:11.214 --> 00:13:12.780 align:middle line:84%
For the first time in my
life, I was determined

00:13:12.780 --> 00:13:14.670 align:middle line:90%
not to screw up what I had.

00:13:14.670 --> 00:13:16.890 align:middle line:90%
Unlike before.

00:13:16.890 --> 00:13:19.030 align:middle line:90%
Don't take it personally.

00:13:19.030 --> 00:13:23.510 align:middle line:90%
It's like I just grew up.

00:13:23.510 --> 00:13:26.170 align:middle line:84%
I never thought I'd
hear you say that.

00:13:26.170 --> 00:13:27.811 align:middle line:84%
You wouldn't even
recognize me anymore.

00:13:27.811 --> 00:13:29.660 align:middle line:84%
I do the garden.
I cut the grass.

00:13:29.660 --> 00:13:31.360 align:middle line:90%
No way.

00:13:31.360 --> 00:13:33.380 align:middle line:84%
-I hardly believe it myself.
-Dog?

00:13:33.380 --> 00:13:34.120 align:middle line:90%
Cat?

00:13:34.120 --> 00:13:35.310 align:middle line:90%
Two dogs.

00:13:35.310 --> 00:13:36.310 align:middle line:90%
Golden retrievers.

00:13:36.310 --> 00:13:37.110 align:middle line:90%
But no kids?

00:13:37.110 --> 00:13:39.330 align:middle line:84%
Mm-mm.
No, we decided not.

00:13:39.330 --> 00:13:40.195 align:middle line:90%
At least not for a while.

00:13:40.195 --> 00:13:44.750 align:middle line:90%


00:13:44.750 --> 00:13:48.210 align:middle line:84%
You know, I was really
scared to see you again.

00:13:48.210 --> 00:13:50.190 align:middle line:90%
KATHERINE: Why?

00:13:50.190 --> 00:13:53.010 align:middle line:84%
Afraid of old
feelings, I guess.

00:13:53.010 --> 00:13:55.062 align:middle line:90%
Afraid of the first few words.

00:13:55.062 --> 00:13:56.760 align:middle line:84%
Afraid of the way that
I might look at you,

00:13:56.760 --> 00:13:59.600 align:middle line:84%
or the way that you
might look at me.

00:13:59.600 --> 00:14:02.710 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: So how
does it feel now?

00:14:02.710 --> 00:14:07.220 align:middle line:84%
It feels like no time
has passed at all.

00:14:07.220 --> 00:14:09.990 align:middle line:90%
Same cafe.

00:14:09.990 --> 00:14:12.390 align:middle line:84%
Maybe we should go to the park.
-I don't know.

00:14:12.390 --> 00:14:13.785 align:middle line:90%
That might be too much.

00:14:13.785 --> 00:14:15.885 align:middle line:84%
I thought that was the point of
this visit-- to heal the past.

00:14:15.885 --> 00:14:18.330 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: I guess
it is part of it.

00:14:18.330 --> 00:14:19.800 align:middle line:84%
-What's the other part?
-Don't worry.

00:14:19.800 --> 00:14:21.080 align:middle line:90%
We'll get to that later.

00:14:21.080 --> 00:14:23.430 align:middle line:90%
FREDRICK: Ah, mystery.

00:14:23.430 --> 00:14:25.170 align:middle line:84%
How does it feel to
have the tables turned?

00:14:25.170 --> 00:14:26.670 align:middle line:90%
You thought I was mysterious?

00:14:26.670 --> 00:14:27.650 align:middle line:90%
I'm shooting for transparent.

00:14:27.650 --> 00:14:29.320 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: I'm not
trying to be mysterious.

00:14:29.320 --> 00:14:31.381 align:middle line:84%
I just don't want
it to get too heavy.

00:14:31.381 --> 00:14:32.080 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't have to.

00:14:32.080 --> 00:14:35.070 align:middle line:84%
Good, because I wanna
look back on this fondly.

00:14:35.070 --> 00:14:36.320 align:middle line:90%
FREDRICK: So how's it so far?

00:14:36.320 --> 00:14:37.909 align:middle line:84%
So far, so good.
It feels familiar.

00:14:37.909 --> 00:14:43.100 align:middle line:90%


00:14:43.100 --> 00:14:46.250 align:middle line:84%
You know, I haven't been
back to Ashland since I left.

00:14:46.250 --> 00:14:47.460 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, I moved about
four years ago.

00:14:47.460 --> 00:14:49.367 align:middle line:90%
I moved down to Sacramento.

00:14:49.367 --> 00:14:50.200 align:middle line:90%
That's where I met Susan.

00:14:50.200 --> 00:14:51.410 align:middle line:90%
Then we moved to the Bay Area.

00:14:51.410 --> 00:14:52.690 align:middle line:90%
I'm still in Phoenix.

00:14:52.690 --> 00:14:53.900 align:middle line:84%
I lived with my
sister for a while.

00:14:53.900 --> 00:14:55.770 align:middle line:90%
And then I got my own house.

00:14:55.770 --> 00:14:57.570 align:middle line:84%
I'm dying to hear what
happened to your book.

00:14:57.570 --> 00:14:58.590 align:middle line:90%
KATHERINE: Nothing, really.

00:14:58.590 --> 00:14:59.410 align:middle line:90%
I self-published.

00:14:59.410 --> 00:15:01.330 align:middle line:90%
I did an internet thing.

00:15:01.330 --> 00:15:03.724 align:middle line:84%
I never could get a publisher
interested in it, though.

00:15:03.724 --> 00:15:05.790 align:middle line:84%
That's the thing that made me
fall in love with you at first.

00:15:05.790 --> 00:15:07.860 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't believe what
a great writer you are.

00:15:07.860 --> 00:15:09.766 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: Why'd you
never finish reading it?

00:15:09.766 --> 00:15:11.400 align:middle line:90%
I read most of it.

00:15:11.400 --> 00:15:14.100 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: But you
never finished it.

00:15:14.100 --> 00:15:17.172 align:middle line:84%
It was just before I headed
off to Australia, you remember?

00:15:17.172 --> 00:15:18.305 align:middle line:84%
You had just
finished a new draft,

00:15:18.305 --> 00:15:21.150 align:middle line:84%
and you told me not to finish
reading until I got down there.

00:15:21.150 --> 00:15:23.170 align:middle line:84%
Then you broke up
with me a week before.

00:15:23.170 --> 00:15:24.200 align:middle line:90%
I wasn't gonna read it then.

00:15:24.200 --> 00:15:25.620 align:middle line:84%
Ah, you had a whole
year before that.

00:15:25.620 --> 00:15:26.230 align:middle line:84%
FREDRICK: I'm not trying
to make up excuses.

00:15:26.230 --> 00:15:27.660 align:middle line:84%
It just didn't feel
very good back then.

00:15:27.660 --> 00:15:30.710 align:middle line:84%
Look, you said that there are
certain things that you regret.

00:15:30.710 --> 00:15:32.725 align:middle line:84%
That's one of the
things I regret.

00:15:32.725 --> 00:15:34.325 align:middle line:84%
There are lots of ways I
didn't give everything,

00:15:34.325 --> 00:15:35.300 align:middle line:90%
even though I wanted to.

00:15:35.300 --> 00:15:38.210 align:middle line:90%


00:15:38.210 --> 00:15:39.540 align:middle line:90%
What?

00:15:39.540 --> 00:15:42.870 align:middle line:84%
Remember that time I
got you that old bike?

00:15:42.870 --> 00:15:45.800 align:middle line:84%
And I wanted to go
riding all the time.

00:15:45.800 --> 00:15:47.950 align:middle line:84%
You went one, and I don't
think you ever went again.

00:15:47.950 --> 00:15:49.830 align:middle line:84%
You kept saying
that you felt silly.

00:15:49.830 --> 00:15:51.410 align:middle line:90%
I wasn't in shape.

00:15:51.410 --> 00:15:53.270 align:middle line:84%
You worked my ass up and
down those hills so hard,

00:15:53.270 --> 00:15:54.770 align:middle line:84%
I thought I was
going to fall off.

00:15:54.770 --> 00:15:56.650 align:middle line:90%
You're in good shape now.

00:15:56.650 --> 00:15:58.220 align:middle line:90%
FREDRICK: Thank god.

00:15:58.220 --> 00:16:00.270 align:middle line:84%
I go to the gym a
couple times a week.

00:16:00.270 --> 00:16:01.920 align:middle line:90%
Makes you wonder, doesn't it?

00:16:01.920 --> 00:16:03.360 align:middle line:90%
FREDRICK: What?

00:16:03.360 --> 00:16:07.100 align:middle line:84%
What would happen if we
met now, how we would feel.

00:16:07.100 --> 00:16:08.080 align:middle line:90%
It'd be different.

00:16:08.080 --> 00:16:10.110 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:16:10.110 --> 00:16:11.825 align:middle line:84%
It'd be different because
the people we are now

00:16:11.825 --> 00:16:16.160 align:middle line:84%
were created, at least in part,
by us being together back then.

00:16:16.160 --> 00:16:19.367 align:middle line:84%
If we'd never met, I
might be a big fat slob.

00:16:19.367 --> 00:16:20.100 align:middle line:90%
KATHERINE: I doubt it.

00:16:20.100 --> 00:16:21.720 align:middle line:90%
Don't.

00:16:21.720 --> 00:16:23.360 align:middle line:84%
You were a pretty big
influence on my life.

00:16:23.360 --> 00:16:26.040 align:middle line:90%


00:16:26.040 --> 00:16:28.517 align:middle line:84%
I thought that-- I thought
if I changed enough,

00:16:28.517 --> 00:16:29.350 align:middle line:90%
you might even come back.

00:16:29.350 --> 00:16:33.410 align:middle line:90%


00:16:33.410 --> 00:16:35.677 align:middle line:90%
Really?

00:16:35.677 --> 00:16:36.810 align:middle line:84%
I started working
on it six years

00:16:36.810 --> 00:16:39.170 align:middle line:90%
ago, right after you left.

00:16:39.170 --> 00:16:42.270 align:middle line:84%
I knew that I wanted to make
myself into a better person,

00:16:42.270 --> 00:16:43.570 align:middle line:84%
so I did something
every day that would

00:16:43.570 --> 00:16:44.999 align:middle line:90%
make me into a better man.

00:16:44.999 --> 00:16:46.665 align:middle line:84%
Some where in the back of
my mind, I thought you'd

00:16:46.665 --> 00:16:48.400 align:middle line:84%
move back to Ashland and
see how much I changed.

00:16:48.400 --> 00:16:50.170 align:middle line:84%
But you have to
start by accepting

00:16:50.170 --> 00:16:52.630 align:middle line:90%
yourself for who you are.

00:16:52.630 --> 00:16:54.240 align:middle line:84%
You can change your
face and your body,

00:16:54.240 --> 00:16:55.670 align:middle line:84%
but if you don't
change your attitude,

00:16:55.670 --> 00:16:57.790 align:middle line:90%
it doesn't make any difference.

00:16:57.790 --> 00:17:00.220 align:middle line:84%
How many women, or
men, for that matter,

00:17:00.220 --> 00:17:01.900 align:middle line:84%
get plastic surgery
over and over

00:17:01.900 --> 00:17:05.470 align:middle line:90%
and still don't like themselves?

00:17:05.470 --> 00:17:07.859 align:middle line:90%
So no more books?

00:17:07.859 --> 00:17:10.589 align:middle line:84%
It's funny you should ask,
because I've been working

00:17:10.589 --> 00:17:12.650 align:middle line:90%
on one for a couple months now.

00:17:12.650 --> 00:17:14.079 align:middle line:90%
FREDRICK: What's it about?

00:17:14.079 --> 00:17:16.150 align:middle line:84%
Well, my last one
was about my mother,

00:17:16.150 --> 00:17:17.250 align:middle line:84%
and probably didn't
get published

00:17:17.250 --> 00:17:18.380 align:middle line:90%
because it was too intense.

00:17:18.380 --> 00:17:22.170 align:middle line:84%
So I decided to pick
a lighter topic.

00:17:22.170 --> 00:17:24.770 align:middle line:90%
Are you gonna tell me?

00:17:24.770 --> 00:17:26.910 align:middle line:90%
It's about us.

00:17:26.910 --> 00:17:28.060 align:middle line:90%
What?

00:17:28.060 --> 00:17:31.720 align:middle line:10%
KATHERINE: That's one of
the reasons I contacted you.

00:17:31.720 --> 00:17:34.060 align:middle line:10%
It's about our relationship--
everything that happened,

00:17:34.060 --> 00:17:36.700 align:middle line:10%
and where it took us.

00:17:36.700 --> 00:17:39.330 align:middle line:84%
That's one of the reasons
I wanted to contact you.

00:17:39.330 --> 00:17:41.530 align:middle line:84%
At first, I thought I could make
up the where it took us part,

00:17:41.530 --> 00:17:44.490 align:middle line:84%
but the more I started writing,
the more I realized that I

00:17:44.490 --> 00:17:46.430 align:middle line:90%
needed to find out the truth.

00:17:46.430 --> 00:17:49.820 align:middle line:84%
You know, where you are
and what you're doing.

00:17:49.820 --> 00:17:53.435 align:middle line:84%
So this is all a
part of your research?

00:17:53.435 --> 00:17:56.600 align:middle line:90%


00:17:56.600 --> 00:17:59.980 align:middle line:90%
I guess it was at first.

00:17:59.980 --> 00:18:01.270 align:middle line:84%
But it made me
curious, you know?

00:18:01.270 --> 00:18:04.860 align:middle line:84%
And I'd be lying if I said it
didn't stir my heart a little.

00:18:04.860 --> 00:18:07.280 align:middle line:90%
Stirred your heart.

00:18:07.280 --> 00:18:09.605 align:middle line:84%
You always act like I'm
some kind of snow queen.

00:18:09.605 --> 00:18:11.050 align:middle line:84%
You're not the only
one who had feelings

00:18:11.050 --> 00:18:12.327 align:middle line:90%
about what happened between us.

00:18:12.327 --> 00:18:13.660 align:middle line:84%
Well, that's the way
it felt sometimes.

00:18:13.660 --> 00:18:15.640 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: That's because
you never understood me.

00:18:15.640 --> 00:18:16.810 align:middle line:90%
It was always about you.

00:18:16.810 --> 00:18:19.840 align:middle line:90%


00:18:19.840 --> 00:18:22.006 align:middle line:90%
I did love you.

00:18:22.006 --> 00:18:24.790 align:middle line:90%
But--

00:18:24.790 --> 00:18:25.690 align:middle line:90%
FREDRICK: Don't stop there.

00:18:25.690 --> 00:18:30.980 align:middle line:90%


00:18:30.980 --> 00:18:33.580 align:middle line:90%
I had to learn to love myself.

00:18:33.580 --> 00:18:35.220 align:middle line:84%
You can't expect someone
else to do that for you.

00:18:35.220 --> 00:18:36.420 align:middle line:90%
It has to come from inside.

00:18:36.420 --> 00:18:38.320 align:middle line:90%
FREDRICK: Mm.

00:18:38.320 --> 00:18:39.300 align:middle line:90%
That's a nice concept.

00:18:39.300 --> 00:18:40.470 align:middle line:84%
But you know, the bottom
line is you couldn't

00:18:40.470 --> 00:18:41.770 align:middle line:84%
stay in a relationship
with me for more

00:18:41.770 --> 00:18:44.580 align:middle line:90%
than two months at a time.

00:18:44.580 --> 00:18:47.030 align:middle line:84%
One day, it would be the most
amazing time of our lives.

00:18:47.030 --> 00:18:49.450 align:middle line:90%
And the next day, it was over.

00:18:49.450 --> 00:18:51.640 align:middle line:84%
How many times did
you break up with me?

00:18:51.640 --> 00:18:52.500 align:middle line:90%
Five?

00:18:52.500 --> 00:18:53.870 align:middle line:90%
It was only three.

00:18:53.870 --> 00:18:55.570 align:middle line:84%
FREDRICK: Yeah, but there
were two other times when

00:18:55.570 --> 00:18:56.736 align:middle line:84%
we almost got back
together and you

00:18:56.736 --> 00:18:57.970 align:middle line:90%
pulled the plug right before.

00:18:57.970 --> 00:18:59.941 align:middle line:84%
Those don't count as
two separate times.

00:18:59.941 --> 00:19:03.270 align:middle line:10%
Fine.
I'll put them together for one.

00:19:03.270 --> 00:19:05.350 align:middle line:84%
Obviously, it seemed
like it was about you.

00:19:05.350 --> 00:19:07.390 align:middle line:84%
But I have a different
perspective on it now.

00:19:07.390 --> 00:19:09.870 align:middle line:10%
Now, you realize it
was all about you.

00:19:09.870 --> 00:19:11.600 align:middle line:84%
Don't use that to
try to make yourself

00:19:11.600 --> 00:19:12.710 align:middle line:90%
sound like the innocent one.

00:19:12.710 --> 00:19:14.634 align:middle line:84%
You should be saying
the same thing.

00:19:14.634 --> 00:19:15.900 align:middle line:84%
I should be saying
it's all about me?

00:19:15.900 --> 00:19:17.155 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: Exactly.
-Wait a minute.

00:19:17.155 --> 00:19:17.540 align:middle line:90%
Wait a minute.

00:19:17.540 --> 00:19:18.806 align:middle line:84%
That's what you say
that I always say.

00:19:18.806 --> 00:19:20.920 align:middle line:90%
It's always about me, right?

00:19:20.920 --> 00:19:21.810 align:middle line:90%
Don't try to confuse me.

00:19:21.810 --> 00:19:23.550 align:middle line:90%
You know what I'm talking about.

00:19:23.550 --> 00:19:25.710 align:middle line:90%
Don't confuse you?

00:19:25.710 --> 00:19:27.730 align:middle line:90%
Women love to say that to men.

00:19:27.730 --> 00:19:29.580 align:middle line:84%
Do you realize how
simple men are?

00:19:29.580 --> 00:19:30.810 align:middle line:84%
Women are the ones
who are complex.

00:19:30.810 --> 00:19:32.320 align:middle line:84%
You say one thing, and
then a minute later,

00:19:32.320 --> 00:19:34.970 align:middle line:84%
you go off in the
opposite direction.

00:19:34.970 --> 00:19:37.170 align:middle line:90%
It's called nonlinear logic.

00:19:37.170 --> 00:19:38.861 align:middle line:84%
Women used to get burned
at the stake for that.

00:19:38.861 --> 00:19:40.560 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, by men who couldn't
understand what the hell

00:19:40.560 --> 00:19:41.890 align:middle line:90%
they were talking about.

00:19:41.890 --> 00:19:43.640 align:middle line:84%
Just because a
thought isn't rational

00:19:43.640 --> 00:19:47.840 align:middle line:84%
doesn't mean that it's not true.
Wait a minute.

00:19:47.840 --> 00:19:49.346 align:middle line:90%
What were we talking about?

00:19:49.346 --> 00:19:50.680 align:middle line:84%
How did you get me
off the subject?

00:19:50.680 --> 00:19:52.320 align:middle line:84%
Well, if you're so
nonlinear, being off

00:19:52.320 --> 00:19:53.720 align:middle line:84%
the subject shouldn't
be a problem.

00:19:53.720 --> 00:19:55.780 align:middle line:90%
What were we talking about?

00:19:55.780 --> 00:19:57.530 align:middle line:84%
I think that you said
that you had realized

00:19:57.530 --> 00:19:58.700 align:middle line:90%
that it was all about you.

00:19:58.700 --> 00:19:59.711 align:middle line:90%
KATHERINE: I don't think so.

00:19:59.711 --> 00:20:00.910 align:middle line:84%
I think I was saying
that you should

00:20:00.910 --> 00:20:03.070 align:middle line:90%
be saying the same thing.

00:20:03.070 --> 00:20:04.540 align:middle line:90%
Blame myself?

00:20:04.540 --> 00:20:06.750 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: It's not
about blaming anyone.

00:20:06.750 --> 00:20:08.910 align:middle line:84%
Ultimately, you have
to take responsibility

00:20:08.910 --> 00:20:11.660 align:middle line:90%
for your own experiences.

00:20:11.660 --> 00:20:13.260 align:middle line:84%
It's the only way we're
going to learn anything.

00:20:13.260 --> 00:20:16.112 align:middle line:84%
And of course, learning
is what it's all about.

00:20:16.112 --> 00:20:17.430 align:middle line:90%
You're so damn cynical.

00:20:17.430 --> 00:20:18.745 align:middle line:84%
Of course that's
what it's all about.

00:20:18.745 --> 00:20:22.180 align:middle line:84%
It's better than going through
life thinking you're a victim.

00:20:22.180 --> 00:20:23.680 align:middle line:90%
I don't think I'm a victim.

00:20:23.680 --> 00:20:26.170 align:middle line:84%
I actually think it
was mainly my fault.

00:20:26.170 --> 00:20:26.870 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:20:26.870 --> 00:20:32.890 align:middle line:90%


00:20:32.890 --> 00:20:33.690 align:middle line:90%
You know why.

00:20:33.690 --> 00:20:37.450 align:middle line:90%


00:20:37.450 --> 00:20:38.330 align:middle line:90%
That was just part of it.

00:20:38.330 --> 00:20:39.680 align:middle line:90%
That's not the reason.

00:20:39.680 --> 00:20:41.665 align:middle line:90%
I think it was.

00:20:41.665 --> 00:20:44.670 align:middle line:90%
A pretty big part of it.

00:20:44.670 --> 00:20:46.685 align:middle line:90%
I should never have told you.

00:20:46.685 --> 00:20:47.660 align:middle line:90%
KATHERINE: You think that?

00:20:47.660 --> 00:20:54.305 align:middle line:90%


00:20:54.305 --> 00:20:57.317 align:middle line:84%
The last time that
we got together,

00:20:57.317 --> 00:20:58.850 align:middle line:84%
I thought I was the
luckiest man in the world.

00:20:58.850 --> 00:21:00.065 align:middle line:90%
I'm not kidding.

00:21:00.065 --> 00:21:02.460 align:middle line:90%
I really thought that.

00:21:02.460 --> 00:21:06.380 align:middle line:84%
But at the same time, there was
this aching feeling inside me,

00:21:06.380 --> 00:21:08.710 align:middle line:84%
because I knew I had to
risk everything and tell you

00:21:08.710 --> 00:21:10.950 align:middle line:90%
what I'd done a year earlier.

00:21:10.950 --> 00:21:13.610 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise, having
you back didn't

00:21:13.610 --> 00:21:14.910 align:middle line:90%
seem to make any difference.

00:21:14.910 --> 00:21:16.850 align:middle line:90%
That's not what broke us up.

00:21:16.850 --> 00:21:17.850 align:middle line:90%
Deep down, it probably did.

00:21:17.850 --> 00:21:19.150 align:middle line:84%
I think it planted
a seed in your mind,

00:21:19.150 --> 00:21:21.050 align:middle line:84%
and I don't think you were
able to trust me after that.

00:21:21.050 --> 00:21:22.490 align:middle line:84%
It was a big risk
you took telling me.

00:21:22.490 --> 00:21:24.930 align:middle line:90%
FREDRICK: Mmhm.

00:21:24.930 --> 00:21:26.630 align:middle line:90%
Probably wouldn't do it again.

00:21:26.630 --> 00:21:28.433 align:middle line:90%
KATHERINE: You would.

00:21:28.433 --> 00:21:31.139 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:21:31.139 --> 00:21:33.823 align:middle line:84%
If it meant holding onto
you, I probably would

00:21:33.823 --> 00:21:36.110 align:middle line:90%
have kept it inside forever.

00:21:36.110 --> 00:21:37.680 align:middle line:84%
Those things never
stay inside forever.

00:21:37.680 --> 00:21:42.215 align:middle line:84%
They always have a way of
coming out, one way or another.

00:21:42.215 --> 00:21:43.840 align:middle line:90%
Is all this in your book?

00:21:43.840 --> 00:21:44.580 align:middle line:90%
Of course.

00:21:44.580 --> 00:21:45.690 align:middle line:90%
Oh, great.

00:21:45.690 --> 00:21:46.850 align:middle line:90%
But not the way you think.

00:21:46.850 --> 00:21:49.710 align:middle line:84%
That was probably the bravest
thing you've ever done.

00:21:49.710 --> 00:21:51.146 align:middle line:90%
Definitely.

00:21:51.146 --> 00:21:54.540 align:middle line:84%
Going into a war zone was
nothing compared to that.

00:21:54.540 --> 00:21:58.310 align:middle line:84%
And it helped make you the
incredible person you are now.

00:21:58.310 --> 00:22:01.276 align:middle line:84%
I always felt like I cheated
more on myself than you.

00:22:01.276 --> 00:22:03.064 align:middle line:84%
I thought if I can
work it out inside,

00:22:03.064 --> 00:22:04.230 align:middle line:84%
then I don't even
have to tell you.

00:22:04.230 --> 00:22:06.470 align:middle line:84%
But the funny
thing was, the more

00:22:06.470 --> 00:22:08.600 align:middle line:84%
that I worked it
out inside, the more

00:22:08.600 --> 00:22:10.310 align:middle line:90%
I knew I needed to tell you.

00:22:10.310 --> 00:22:12.330 align:middle line:84%
It was like being redeemed and
condemned at the same time.

00:22:12.330 --> 00:22:15.350 align:middle line:90%


00:22:15.350 --> 00:22:19.850 align:middle line:90%
Really, Fredrick, I'm serious.

00:22:19.850 --> 00:22:23.000 align:middle line:90%
That's not what broke us up.

00:22:23.000 --> 00:22:26.590 align:middle line:84%
I had to find myself.
I don't know.

00:22:26.590 --> 00:22:28.200 align:middle line:84%
Maybe it would be
different if it were today.

00:22:28.200 --> 00:22:30.210 align:middle line:90%
Who knows?

00:22:30.210 --> 00:22:31.370 align:middle line:84%
But you have to
get over thinking

00:22:31.370 --> 00:22:36.030 align:middle line:90%
that it was your fault.

00:22:36.030 --> 00:22:38.850 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't matter anyway.

00:22:38.850 --> 00:22:40.970 align:middle line:84%
Everything works out the
way it's supposed to.

00:22:40.970 --> 00:22:41.940 align:middle line:90%
Of course it does.

00:22:41.940 --> 00:22:42.740 align:middle line:90%
You're happy, right?

00:22:42.740 --> 00:22:45.535 align:middle line:90%
FREDRICK: I'm really happy.

00:22:45.535 --> 00:22:46.916 align:middle line:84%
I hope you get a
chance to meet Susan.

00:22:46.916 --> 00:22:47.615 align:middle line:90%
[CATHERINE EXHALES]

00:22:47.615 --> 00:22:49.127 align:middle line:84%
You guys would really
like each other.

00:22:49.127 --> 00:22:50.438 align:middle line:90%
KATHERINE: Mm.

00:22:50.438 --> 00:22:51.312 align:middle line:90%
What?

00:22:51.312 --> 00:22:54.030 align:middle line:90%
You wouldn't want to meet her?

00:22:54.030 --> 00:22:57.600 align:middle line:84%
Don't you think it would
be a little awkward for her?

00:22:57.600 --> 00:22:59.360 align:middle line:84%
FREDRICK: I think she
understands what's going on.

00:22:59.360 --> 00:23:01.120 align:middle line:90%
I just hope you understand.

00:23:01.120 --> 00:23:02.460 align:middle line:90%
I do.

00:23:02.460 --> 00:23:05.550 align:middle line:84%
Unless there's something
you haven't told me.

00:23:05.550 --> 00:23:08.950 align:middle line:90%
Actually, there is.

00:23:08.950 --> 00:23:11.730 align:middle line:90%
You have a son.

00:23:11.730 --> 00:23:12.522 align:middle line:90%
What?

00:23:12.522 --> 00:23:13.880 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHING]

00:23:13.880 --> 00:23:14.600 align:middle line:90%
I'm just kidding.

00:23:14.600 --> 00:23:16.086 align:middle line:84%
No, there's nothing
I haven't told you.

00:23:16.086 --> 00:23:18.500 align:middle line:84%
FREDRICK: Jesus.
Don't do that to me.

00:23:18.500 --> 00:23:20.500 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: What?
Would that have been so bad?

00:23:20.500 --> 00:23:22.330 align:middle line:84%
Me having a son with you
that I never knew about?

00:23:22.330 --> 00:23:23.640 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, that would be a shock.

00:23:23.640 --> 00:23:25.490 align:middle line:90%
But it wouldn't be that.

00:23:25.490 --> 00:23:26.580 align:middle line:90%
Of course it wouldn't be bad.

00:23:26.580 --> 00:23:29.380 align:middle line:90%
It would be-- I don't even know.

00:23:29.380 --> 00:23:30.700 align:middle line:84%
Why are we even
talking about this?

00:23:30.700 --> 00:23:32.330 align:middle line:84%
I just wanted to
see how you'd react.

00:23:32.330 --> 00:23:33.190 align:middle line:90%
[FREDRICK LAUGHING]

00:23:33.190 --> 00:23:35.660 align:middle line:84%
Best leave that out when
you get home to Susan.

00:23:35.660 --> 00:23:38.641 align:middle line:84%
Oh, she's just down the
street at the hotel waiting.

00:23:38.641 --> 00:23:39.340 align:middle line:90%
She's here?

00:23:39.340 --> 00:23:41.800 align:middle line:84%
I thought you said
you were alone.

00:23:41.800 --> 00:23:44.180 align:middle line:84%
No, I said that she knew
that I had to be alone.

00:23:44.180 --> 00:23:47.190 align:middle line:84%
But I didn't come
here without her.

00:23:47.190 --> 00:23:49.800 align:middle line:84%
Even now, someone's intruding
on our time together.

00:23:49.800 --> 00:23:50.800 align:middle line:90%
FREDRICK: She isn't intruding.

00:23:50.800 --> 00:23:51.633 align:middle line:90%
She's here support to me.

00:23:51.633 --> 00:23:53.110 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, like all the rest.

00:23:53.110 --> 00:23:54.410 align:middle line:84%
FREDRICK: What's that
supposed to mean?

00:23:54.410 --> 00:23:55.500 align:middle line:90%
What rest?

00:23:55.500 --> 00:23:56.400 align:middle line:90%
Nothing.

00:23:56.400 --> 00:23:59.300 align:middle line:84%
Forget it.
-Kat.

00:23:59.300 --> 00:24:05.820 align:middle line:90%


00:24:05.820 --> 00:24:07.120 align:middle line:84%
I'm sorry, I didn't
mean to imply you--

00:24:07.120 --> 00:24:08.811 align:middle line:84%
It's OK.
It's fine.

00:24:08.811 --> 00:24:09.510 align:middle line:90%
I just misunderstood.

00:24:09.510 --> 00:24:16.290 align:middle line:90%


00:24:16.290 --> 00:24:19.130 align:middle line:84%
When you called and asked
if we could get together,

00:24:19.130 --> 00:24:21.810 align:middle line:84%
it was like this weight
lifted off my heart that I

00:24:21.810 --> 00:24:24.080 align:middle line:90%
didn't even know was there.

00:24:24.080 --> 00:24:25.240 align:middle line:84%
I had grown so
used to it, it had

00:24:25.240 --> 00:24:27.450 align:middle line:90%
become this normal part of me.

00:24:27.450 --> 00:24:30.420 align:middle line:90%
Susan understood that.

00:24:30.420 --> 00:24:32.090 align:middle line:84%
I think she must have
felt it at all along.

00:24:32.090 --> 00:24:34.670 align:middle line:84%
It's pretty incredible
that she's here at all.

00:24:34.670 --> 00:24:36.831 align:middle line:90%
FREDRICK: That's how she is.

00:24:36.831 --> 00:24:40.110 align:middle line:90%
I'm lucky.

00:24:40.110 --> 00:24:42.150 align:middle line:90%
I'm glad.

00:24:42.150 --> 00:24:42.908 align:middle line:90%
You deserve it.

00:24:42.908 --> 00:24:51.210 align:middle line:90%


00:24:51.210 --> 00:24:53.256 align:middle line:84%
FREDRICK: So is there a plot
to this book you're writing?

00:24:53.256 --> 00:24:55.310 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: It's
about falling in love

00:24:55.310 --> 00:24:57.730 align:middle line:84%
and wondering who it is
you fell in love with

00:24:57.730 --> 00:25:01.200 align:middle line:84%
and then realizing that
it was yourself all along.

00:25:01.200 --> 00:25:02.020 align:middle line:90%
You've lost me.

00:25:02.020 --> 00:25:03.760 align:middle line:90%
It's what I just said.

00:25:03.760 --> 00:25:05.290 align:middle line:84%
We need another person,
and a part of us

00:25:05.290 --> 00:25:07.000 align:middle line:84%
thinks that they have
something that we don't have

00:25:07.000 --> 00:25:08.450 align:middle line:90%
anymore-- something we need.

00:25:08.450 --> 00:25:10.690 align:middle line:84%
And then all of our
hormones kick in,

00:25:10.690 --> 00:25:13.190 align:middle line:84%
and we move hell and high
water to get that thing,

00:25:13.190 --> 00:25:15.810 align:middle line:90%
and then not to lose it.

00:25:15.810 --> 00:25:18.940 align:middle line:84%
But that just makes us
unsatisfied, you know?

00:25:18.940 --> 00:25:20.330 align:middle line:84%
It makes us crave
the real thing even

00:25:20.330 --> 00:25:22.290 align:middle line:84%
more, which is why
so many marriages

00:25:22.290 --> 00:25:24.740 align:middle line:90%
dissolve into complacency.

00:25:24.740 --> 00:25:26.820 align:middle line:84%
Which leaves the
obvious question.

00:25:26.820 --> 00:25:28.850 align:middle line:84%
What is the thing that
we think we don't have

00:25:28.850 --> 00:25:30.480 align:middle line:90%
that we search for in others?

00:25:30.480 --> 00:25:31.560 align:middle line:90%
Let me guess.

00:25:31.560 --> 00:25:32.650 align:middle line:90%
Great sex.

00:25:32.650 --> 00:25:34.140 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:25:34.140 --> 00:25:36.020 align:middle line:90%
Understanding, self-knowledge.

00:25:36.020 --> 00:25:37.419 align:middle line:84%
-Understanding?
-Yeah.

00:25:37.419 --> 00:25:38.417 align:middle line:90%
This is nonlinear, right?

00:25:38.417 --> 00:25:39.650 align:middle line:84%
That's what we're
all searching for.

00:25:39.650 --> 00:25:41.170 align:middle line:90%
To understand who we are.

00:25:41.170 --> 00:25:43.070 align:middle line:84%
Well, how are we supposed to
find that in somebody else?

00:25:43.070 --> 00:25:44.310 align:middle line:90%
You can't, stupid.

00:25:44.310 --> 00:25:46.200 align:middle line:90%
That's the point.

00:25:46.200 --> 00:25:49.040 align:middle line:90%
Though we keep trying.

00:25:49.040 --> 00:25:52.180 align:middle line:84%
Somewhere along the way,
we think we lost something.

00:25:52.180 --> 00:25:54.660 align:middle line:84%
And we keep searching
outside of ourselves for it.

00:25:54.660 --> 00:25:57.720 align:middle line:84%
What if the thing we thought we
lost was inside us all along?

00:25:57.720 --> 00:26:00.820 align:middle line:84%
We just have to look
at the right place.

00:26:00.820 --> 00:26:03.900 align:middle line:84%
I'm having a hard time
seeing how this applies to us.

00:26:03.900 --> 00:26:07.292 align:middle line:84%
You could never understand why
I kept breaking up with you.

00:26:07.292 --> 00:26:10.070 align:middle line:90%
It had nothing to do with you.

00:26:10.070 --> 00:26:11.950 align:middle line:84%
I kept looking for you
to give me something

00:26:11.950 --> 00:26:13.600 align:middle line:84%
that I didn't think
I had anymore.

00:26:13.600 --> 00:26:15.480 align:middle line:84%
And when you didn't,
I became frustrated,

00:26:15.480 --> 00:26:19.020 align:middle line:84%
and that wasn't
your job I really

00:26:19.020 --> 00:26:20.580 align:middle line:84%
do think we were
meant to be together,

00:26:20.580 --> 00:26:21.780 align:middle line:84%
just not for the
reasons we thought.

00:26:21.780 --> 00:26:22.735 align:middle line:84%
Whoa, wait a minute.
Wait a minute.

00:26:22.735 --> 00:26:24.390 align:middle line:84%
Wait a minute.
What do you mean by that?

00:26:24.390 --> 00:26:26.090 align:middle line:84%
I don't recall every
feeling that from you.

00:26:26.090 --> 00:26:27.110 align:middle line:90%
That's unfair, Fredrick.

00:26:27.110 --> 00:26:28.720 align:middle line:84%
I know you take
everything personal.

00:26:28.720 --> 00:26:30.874 align:middle line:84%
But don't make it
sound so horrible.

00:26:30.874 --> 00:26:32.740 align:middle line:84%
There are lessons we could
only learn by being together,

00:26:32.740 --> 00:26:34.690 align:middle line:90%
no matter how it turned out.

00:26:34.690 --> 00:26:36.210 align:middle line:84%
I don't even remember
what I thought.

00:26:36.210 --> 00:26:38.026 align:middle line:90%
Yes, you do.

00:26:38.026 --> 00:26:39.930 align:middle line:84%
You thought we were
going to get married

00:26:39.930 --> 00:26:42.510 align:middle line:90%
and live happily ever after.

00:26:42.510 --> 00:26:44.570 align:middle line:90%
I did too for a while.

00:26:44.570 --> 00:26:48.390 align:middle line:84%
And when it didn't work
out, I had to look deeper.

00:26:48.390 --> 00:26:49.960 align:middle line:84%
And at first, I didn't
like what I saw.

00:26:49.960 --> 00:26:55.550 align:middle line:84%
And then I realized that you
were one of my greatest gifts.

00:26:55.550 --> 00:26:57.580 align:middle line:84%
You have a pretty
strange way of showing it.

00:26:57.580 --> 00:27:00.740 align:middle line:90%
Why do you say that?

00:27:00.740 --> 00:27:03.130 align:middle line:84%
Six years have passed,
and I haven't heard a word.

00:27:03.130 --> 00:27:05.570 align:middle line:84%
Then suddenly, you
want to write a book

00:27:05.570 --> 00:27:07.840 align:middle line:84%
about it telling the world
what an amazing gift I was?

00:27:07.840 --> 00:27:09.314 align:middle line:90%
You make it sound so horrible.

00:27:09.314 --> 00:27:10.280 align:middle line:90%
It's not that it's horrible.

00:27:10.280 --> 00:27:13.740 align:middle line:84%
But from my perspective,
it completely sucks.

00:27:13.740 --> 00:27:14.970 align:middle line:84%
You break up with
me for the third

00:27:14.970 --> 00:27:17.734 align:middle line:84%
or the fourth or the fifth time,
depending on how you define it,

00:27:17.734 --> 00:27:19.100 align:middle line:84%
and even though you're
the most important

00:27:19.100 --> 00:27:20.060 align:middle line:84%
person in the world
to me, you decide

00:27:20.060 --> 00:27:20.926 align:middle line:90%
we can't even communicate.

00:27:20.926 --> 00:27:23.417 align:middle line:90%


00:27:23.417 --> 00:27:24.750 align:middle line:84%
I don't wanna keep
beating a dead horse,

00:27:24.750 --> 00:27:26.894 align:middle line:84%
but I didn't know
what to do with that.

00:27:26.894 --> 00:27:28.160 align:middle line:84%
It was like somebody
died and I didn't

00:27:28.160 --> 00:27:29.359 align:middle line:84%
get a chance to
tell them how much I

00:27:29.359 --> 00:27:31.900 align:middle line:90%
loved them or missed them.

00:27:31.900 --> 00:27:33.640 align:middle line:84%
I'm glad you were able
to go off and have all

00:27:33.640 --> 00:27:34.760 align:middle line:90%
these brilliant realizations.

00:27:34.760 --> 00:27:37.640 align:middle line:90%
But it wasn't the same for me.

00:27:37.640 --> 00:27:39.180 align:middle line:90%
Catherine?

00:27:39.180 --> 00:27:41.270 align:middle line:90%
Is that you?

00:27:41.270 --> 00:27:41.970 align:middle line:90%
It's Mike.

00:27:41.970 --> 00:27:43.003 align:middle line:90%
You probably don't remember me.

00:27:43.003 --> 00:27:44.670 align:middle line:84%
We had a date like
eight years ago.

00:27:44.670 --> 00:27:46.270 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, Mike.
I do.

00:27:46.270 --> 00:27:47.200 align:middle line:90%
How are you?

00:27:47.200 --> 00:27:48.430 align:middle line:90%
MIKE: I'm great.

00:27:48.430 --> 00:27:50.210 align:middle line:84%
I thought you move like
six or seven years ago.

00:27:50.210 --> 00:27:51.280 align:middle line:90%
KATHERINE: I'm in Phoenix now.

00:27:51.280 --> 00:27:52.190 align:middle line:90%
Are you still here?

00:27:52.190 --> 00:27:53.911 align:middle line:84%
Oh, I doubt I'll
ever leave Ashland.

00:27:53.911 --> 00:27:56.280 align:middle line:84%
I'm sorry.
I'm Mike.

00:27:56.280 --> 00:27:57.800 align:middle line:84%
I hope I'm not
interrupting anything.

00:27:57.800 --> 00:27:59.630 align:middle line:84%
FREDRICK: No.
-No.

00:27:59.630 --> 00:28:00.460 align:middle line:90%
Nothing serious.

00:28:00.460 --> 00:28:02.270 align:middle line:84%
This is Fredrick.
MIKE: Right.

00:28:02.270 --> 00:28:04.230 align:middle line:90%
I used to see you around town.

00:28:04.230 --> 00:28:05.480 align:middle line:90%
Are you guys married now?

00:28:05.480 --> 00:28:06.580 align:middle line:84%
You were dating
back then, right?

00:28:06.580 --> 00:28:07.740 align:middle line:90%
KATHERINE: No.

00:28:07.740 --> 00:28:10.420 align:middle line:84%
We're just spending
the afternoon together.

00:28:10.420 --> 00:28:11.900 align:middle line:84%
Well, I don't want
to, uh, get in the way,

00:28:11.900 --> 00:28:16.360 align:middle line:84%
but if you have time, why
don't you, um, give me a call?

00:28:16.360 --> 00:28:17.820 align:middle line:84%
We could have
dinner or something.

00:28:17.820 --> 00:28:20.013 align:middle line:84%
That's my cell
phone on the back.

00:28:20.013 --> 00:28:20.840 align:middle line:90%
KATHERINE: OK.

00:28:20.840 --> 00:28:22.860 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, maybe.

00:28:22.860 --> 00:28:24.552 align:middle line:84%
It was really nice
seeing you again.

00:28:24.552 --> 00:28:26.740 align:middle line:90%
It was nice to see you too.

00:28:26.740 --> 00:28:27.750 align:middle line:90%
Have a great walk.

00:28:27.750 --> 00:28:35.170 align:middle line:90%


00:28:35.170 --> 00:28:36.280 align:middle line:90%
(SARCASTIC) That was fun.

00:28:36.280 --> 00:28:36.980 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, it was.

00:28:36.980 --> 00:28:39.324 align:middle line:90%


00:28:39.324 --> 00:28:40.490 align:middle line:84%
I don't have right
to get jealous.

00:28:40.490 --> 00:28:41.189 align:middle line:90%
You're married.

00:28:41.189 --> 00:28:44.040 align:middle line:90%


00:28:44.040 --> 00:28:45.540 align:middle line:84%
Look, back to what
I was saying before,

00:28:45.540 --> 00:28:48.810 align:middle line:84%
I was holding onto
stuff for six years,

00:28:48.810 --> 00:28:51.610 align:middle line:84%
and I didn't have any
way of letting it go.

00:28:51.610 --> 00:28:55.791 align:middle line:84%
Maybe that was why it was
important for us to meet.

00:28:55.791 --> 00:28:56.490 align:middle line:90%
Maybe.

00:28:56.490 --> 00:29:09.960 align:middle line:90%


00:29:09.960 --> 00:29:13.160 align:middle line:84%
So when I get to
Baghdad, that taxi

00:29:13.160 --> 00:29:15.381 align:middle line:84%
drops me off at this hotel
called the El Rashid.

00:29:15.381 --> 00:29:16.080 align:middle line:90%
Mmhm.

00:29:16.080 --> 00:29:17.740 align:middle line:84%
You gotta remember, I've been
on the road for like two days

00:29:17.740 --> 00:29:18.700 align:middle line:90%
straight.

00:29:18.700 --> 00:29:20.240 align:middle line:84%
And when I get to
Amman, somebody

00:29:20.240 --> 00:29:23.445 align:middle line:84%
tells me I have to take a
taxi all the way into Iraq.

00:29:23.445 --> 00:29:24.280 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't believe it.

00:29:24.280 --> 00:29:26.620 align:middle line:84%
It was like this 12 hour
drive, tiny little car.

00:29:26.620 --> 00:29:28.980 align:middle line:84%
Driver speaks like
three words of English.

00:29:28.980 --> 00:29:31.060 align:middle line:84%
So we finally get to
Baghdad, which is literally

00:29:31.060 --> 00:29:34.060 align:middle line:90%
my first steps onto Iraqi soil.

00:29:34.060 --> 00:29:36.550 align:middle line:84%
And I get out of the cab, and
I'm walking up to the hotel.

00:29:36.550 --> 00:29:39.190 align:middle line:84%
And I look to the floor, and I
see this huge, really well done

00:29:39.190 --> 00:29:40.390 align:middle line:90%
mosaic.

00:29:40.390 --> 00:29:42.460 align:middle line:84%
And then I see these old
Iraqi women spitting on it

00:29:42.460 --> 00:29:45.610 align:middle line:90%
as they pass by.

00:29:45.610 --> 00:29:48.120 align:middle line:84%
And as I'm walking
over it, I see

00:29:48.120 --> 00:29:51.520 align:middle line:84%
that there's this face in the
center of the mosaic-- really

00:29:51.520 --> 00:29:54.560 align:middle line:90%
big, with a snarl on his lips.

00:29:54.560 --> 00:29:56.900 align:middle line:84%
And I think, that
looks just like George

00:29:56.900 --> 00:29:59.370 align:middle line:90%
Bush-- senior, of course.

00:29:59.370 --> 00:30:01.510 align:middle line:84%
And I look back, and
sure enough, it is.

00:30:01.510 --> 00:30:03.150 align:middle line:84%
You have to walk
over George Bush's

00:30:03.150 --> 00:30:04.830 align:middle line:90%
face to get into this hotel.

00:30:04.830 --> 00:30:05.530 align:middle line:90%
You're kidding.

00:30:05.530 --> 00:30:07.310 align:middle line:84%
No, that's not
even the best part.

00:30:07.310 --> 00:30:09.570 align:middle line:84%
Underneath the face in the
mosaic is a sign that reads,

00:30:09.570 --> 00:30:12.670 align:middle line:84%
in English, "Bush
is a criminal."

00:30:12.670 --> 00:30:14.164 align:middle line:84%
Those were your
first steps in Iraq?

00:30:14.164 --> 00:30:15.530 align:middle line:84%
It didn't make me
feel all that welcome.

00:30:15.530 --> 00:30:16.600 align:middle line:90%
I thought, geez.

00:30:16.600 --> 00:30:18.100 align:middle line:84%
Maybe I should tell
everybody I'm a Canadian.

00:30:18.100 --> 00:30:19.155 align:middle line:90%
It's hard to hate Canadians.

00:30:19.155 --> 00:30:22.651 align:middle line:90%


00:30:22.651 --> 00:30:23.350 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:30:23.350 --> 00:30:26.810 align:middle line:84%
I met a few seedy
characters in Toronto.

00:30:26.810 --> 00:30:28.987 align:middle line:90%
So do you miss the danger?

00:30:28.987 --> 00:30:30.220 align:middle line:84%
No, it's not the
danger that I miss.

00:30:30.220 --> 00:30:32.820 align:middle line:84%
It's more the perceived
danger and how

00:30:32.820 --> 00:30:35.810 align:middle line:84%
everybody thought about me when
I went to dangerous places.

00:30:35.810 --> 00:30:38.670 align:middle line:84%
It was never dangerous as
you think it's going to be.

00:30:38.670 --> 00:30:40.870 align:middle line:84%
If you keep your head down
and follow a few basic rules,

00:30:40.870 --> 00:30:42.340 align:middle line:84%
for the most part,
you're going to be fine.

00:30:42.340 --> 00:30:45.780 align:middle line:84%
It's the guys who are always
looking for their big Pulitzer

00:30:45.780 --> 00:30:46.750 align:middle line:90%
Prize winning photo.

00:30:46.750 --> 00:30:48.770 align:middle line:84%
They wind up pushing
the envelope too far

00:30:48.770 --> 00:30:51.580 align:middle line:84%
and getting caught
in the crossfire.

00:30:51.580 --> 00:30:53.600 align:middle line:84%
I do miss people thinking
I'm hot shit because I

00:30:53.600 --> 00:30:55.356 align:middle line:90%
traveled to war zones, though.

00:30:55.356 --> 00:30:57.700 align:middle line:84%
You don't get the same kind
of respect writing stories

00:30:57.700 --> 00:30:59.680 align:middle line:90%
about popcorn.

00:30:59.680 --> 00:31:01.460 align:middle line:90%
I'm glad you stopped, though.

00:31:01.460 --> 00:31:02.960 align:middle line:84%
Every time a conflict
broke out in the world

00:31:02.960 --> 00:31:04.662 align:middle line:90%
I worried about you.

00:31:04.662 --> 00:31:07.040 align:middle line:90%
That's funny.

00:31:07.040 --> 00:31:09.400 align:middle line:90%
KATHERINE: Why?

00:31:09.400 --> 00:31:12.110 align:middle line:84%
Do you remember when I
was heading to Iraq in '98?

00:31:12.110 --> 00:31:15.270 align:middle line:84%
We had just broken up, you had
already cut off communication.

00:31:15.270 --> 00:31:18.331 align:middle line:84%
And I was really
scared about going.

00:31:18.331 --> 00:31:19.710 align:middle line:84%
Usually, I'm fine.
I never worry.

00:31:19.710 --> 00:31:21.040 align:middle line:84%
But there were a lot
of people getting

00:31:21.040 --> 00:31:22.580 align:middle line:90%
shot or kidnapped at the time.

00:31:22.580 --> 00:31:24.776 align:middle line:84%
And I had this terrible
feeling something

00:31:24.776 --> 00:31:27.220 align:middle line:90%
was gonna happen to me.

00:31:27.220 --> 00:31:29.040 align:middle line:84%
So I left a message
on your cellphone

00:31:29.040 --> 00:31:31.071 align:middle line:90%
asking you to call me.

00:31:31.071 --> 00:31:33.070 align:middle line:84%
The idea of going over there
without some kind of completion

00:31:33.070 --> 00:31:34.185 align:middle line:90%
with you made me sick.

00:31:34.185 --> 00:31:35.930 align:middle line:84%
It felt like I was
going to actually

00:31:35.930 --> 00:31:38.370 align:middle line:90%
draw something bad to me.

00:31:38.370 --> 00:31:39.470 align:middle line:84%
All I wanted was
to say good bye.

00:31:39.470 --> 00:31:42.721 align:middle line:84%
No big scene, just a
two minute phone call.

00:31:42.721 --> 00:31:43.420 align:middle line:90%
You never called.

00:31:43.420 --> 00:31:46.077 align:middle line:90%


00:31:46.077 --> 00:31:47.610 align:middle line:84%
I would have been fine
with a email, anything.

00:31:47.610 --> 00:31:51.560 align:middle line:84%
But instead, I wind up
going off to this war zone

00:31:51.560 --> 00:31:53.960 align:middle line:90%
all screwed up inside.

00:31:53.960 --> 00:31:55.836 align:middle line:84%
What do you want
me to say to you?

00:31:55.836 --> 00:31:57.380 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't matter
what you say now.

00:31:57.380 --> 00:31:59.930 align:middle line:90%
That's when I needed it.

00:31:59.930 --> 00:32:02.670 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: Is it all right if
I just say that I was wrong?

00:32:02.670 --> 00:32:04.060 align:middle line:84%
FREDRICK: You're
willing to admit that?

00:32:04.060 --> 00:32:06.150 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't matter
what excuse I use.

00:32:06.150 --> 00:32:08.660 align:middle line:84%
I was feeling what I
was feeling at the time.

00:32:08.660 --> 00:32:09.920 align:middle line:84%
I should have
called, bottom line.

00:32:09.920 --> 00:32:12.650 align:middle line:90%


00:32:12.650 --> 00:32:14.470 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:32:14.470 --> 00:32:16.740 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, that feels better.

00:32:16.740 --> 00:32:19.020 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: You know, if we
look back and second guess

00:32:19.020 --> 00:32:23.870 align:middle line:84%
every choice we ever made, we're
gonna be in for a long battle.

00:32:23.870 --> 00:32:27.981 align:middle line:84%
We all make mistakes--
you, me, and everyone else.

00:32:27.981 --> 00:32:29.970 align:middle line:84%
We're human.
We're all idiots sometimes.

00:32:29.970 --> 00:32:32.720 align:middle line:84%
Do you have any idea
how mad I was about that?

00:32:32.720 --> 00:32:34.894 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: Mad enough to
hold onto it for six years?

00:32:34.894 --> 00:32:36.160 align:middle line:84%
It proved to me
that I wasn't screwed

00:32:36.160 --> 00:32:37.150 align:middle line:90%
up one in the relationship.

00:32:37.150 --> 00:32:38.990 align:middle line:84%
I thought, damn,
if she won't even

00:32:38.990 --> 00:32:42.134 align:middle line:84%
call me when I'm headed
to Iraq, maybe I'm

00:32:42.134 --> 00:32:43.370 align:middle line:90%
not the one with the problem.

00:32:43.370 --> 00:32:44.490 align:middle line:90%
It made you right.

00:32:44.490 --> 00:32:46.070 align:middle line:90%
FREDRICK: Yeah, I guess so.

00:32:46.070 --> 00:32:47.130 align:middle line:90%
KATHERINE: Did that help?

00:32:47.130 --> 00:32:48.679 align:middle line:84%
-Being right?
-Yeah.

00:32:48.679 --> 00:32:49.920 align:middle line:90%
I guess.

00:32:49.920 --> 00:32:53.487 align:middle line:90%
But it wasn't even that.

00:32:53.487 --> 00:32:54.820 align:middle line:84%
I mean, up until that
point, I had never

00:32:54.820 --> 00:32:56.230 align:middle line:84%
been so close to
anybody in my life,

00:32:56.230 --> 00:32:59.070 align:middle line:90%
and then you pulled the plug.

00:32:59.070 --> 00:33:00.270 align:middle line:84%
I needed something
to get over. you.

00:33:00.270 --> 00:33:02.760 align:middle line:84%
I actually needed you
to be a bitch to me.

00:33:02.760 --> 00:33:04.630 align:middle line:90%
Well, did It work?

00:33:04.630 --> 00:33:05.800 align:middle line:90%
For about a week.

00:33:05.800 --> 00:33:07.070 align:middle line:90%
And then what?

00:33:07.070 --> 00:33:11.170 align:middle line:84%
Then, I was right
back where I started.

00:33:11.170 --> 00:33:13.000 align:middle line:84%
It took a year for the
pain in my gut to ease up

00:33:13.000 --> 00:33:15.487 align:middle line:90%
and get you out of my dreams.

00:33:15.487 --> 00:33:16.920 align:middle line:84%
I'd see these women
who reminded me of you,

00:33:16.920 --> 00:33:18.500 align:middle line:84%
and of course, I
was wildly attracted

00:33:18.500 --> 00:33:20.940 align:middle line:90%
to every single one of them.

00:33:20.940 --> 00:33:24.600 align:middle line:84%
There's this Lyle Lovett song
that goes, (SINGING) I married

00:33:24.600 --> 00:33:29.804 align:middle line:90%
her, she looked a lot like you.

00:33:29.804 --> 00:33:31.370 align:middle line:84%
If I could have gotten
with one of those women,

00:33:31.370 --> 00:33:33.370 align:middle line:84%
I would have done
it in a second.

00:33:33.370 --> 00:33:35.190 align:middle line:90%
You didn't jump in with anyone?

00:33:35.190 --> 00:33:37.540 align:middle line:84%
FREDRICK: I wanted
to, but I didn't.

00:33:37.540 --> 00:33:39.710 align:middle line:84%
For the first time
in my life, I decided

00:33:39.710 --> 00:33:41.820 align:middle line:90%
to take a break from women.

00:33:41.820 --> 00:33:42.920 align:middle line:84%
There were lots
of opportunities.

00:33:42.920 --> 00:33:44.840 align:middle line:84%
And I mean lots
of opportunities.

00:33:44.840 --> 00:33:47.317 align:middle line:90%
But I didn't do it.

00:33:47.317 --> 00:33:48.650 align:middle line:84%
And I knew I had to
feel everything that

00:33:48.650 --> 00:33:50.710 align:middle line:90%
was coming my way and not run.

00:33:50.710 --> 00:33:53.970 align:middle line:84%
And first, all I wanted was a
woman to make the pain go away,

00:33:53.970 --> 00:33:57.620 align:middle line:84%
but I knew that
wouldn't have helped.

00:33:57.620 --> 00:34:00.690 align:middle line:84%
So you took the
time to look within.

00:34:00.690 --> 00:34:01.850 align:middle line:90%
As much as I could.

00:34:01.850 --> 00:34:03.215 align:middle line:90%
Into-me-see.

00:34:03.215 --> 00:34:05.238 align:middle line:90%
What's that mean?

00:34:05.238 --> 00:34:06.610 align:middle line:90%
Intimacy.

00:34:06.610 --> 00:34:07.950 align:middle line:90%
Into-me-see.

00:34:07.950 --> 00:34:09.540 align:middle line:90%
That's what intimacy is.

00:34:09.540 --> 00:34:11.340 align:middle line:90%
Looking within.

00:34:11.340 --> 00:34:13.900 align:middle line:84%
We always search for the
answers outside of ourselves.

00:34:13.900 --> 00:34:18.060 align:middle line:84%
But it's all inside.
-What about you?

00:34:18.060 --> 00:34:19.000 align:middle line:90%
What'd you do?

00:34:19.000 --> 00:34:19.940 align:middle line:90%
I told do.

00:34:19.940 --> 00:34:21.710 align:middle line:84%
I had a few relationships,
nothing too dramatic.

00:34:21.710 --> 00:34:22.550 align:middle line:90%
No, no, no.

00:34:22.550 --> 00:34:23.860 align:middle line:84%
You gotta to give
me more than that.

00:34:23.860 --> 00:34:26.730 align:middle line:84%
I just spilled my guts
out all over the sidewalk.

00:34:26.730 --> 00:34:29.949 align:middle line:84%
First, I thought about getting
back with my old boyfriend.

00:34:29.949 --> 00:34:30.650 align:middle line:90%
Christopher?

00:34:30.650 --> 00:34:32.469 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:34:32.469 --> 00:34:34.730 align:middle line:90%
But you can never go back.

00:34:34.730 --> 00:34:37.070 align:middle line:84%
I knew that if I wanted to
get serious with anyone,

00:34:37.070 --> 00:34:39.330 align:middle line:84%
I had to make a
clean break with you.

00:34:39.330 --> 00:34:41.005 align:middle line:90%
I noticed you did that.

00:34:41.005 --> 00:34:44.389 align:middle line:90%
Don't you see why?

00:34:44.389 --> 00:34:47.260 align:middle line:84%
I left Ashland because I
knew as soon as I saw you,

00:34:47.260 --> 00:34:50.000 align:middle line:90%
it would start all over again.

00:34:50.000 --> 00:34:52.420 align:middle line:84%
There's this thing
between us that's

00:34:52.420 --> 00:34:56.790 align:middle line:90%
intangible, like magnets.

00:34:56.790 --> 00:34:59.304 align:middle line:84%
-Do you feel it now?
-Yeah.

00:34:59.304 --> 00:35:02.400 align:middle line:90%
Do you?

00:35:02.400 --> 00:35:03.100 align:middle line:90%
Of course.

00:35:03.100 --> 00:35:12.448 align:middle line:90%


00:35:12.448 --> 00:35:15.400 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: Please
don't [INAUDIBLE].

00:35:15.400 --> 00:35:16.876 align:middle line:90%
FREDRICK: That gigantic cat.

00:35:16.876 --> 00:35:20.110 align:middle line:90%
I know, he's so tiny.

00:35:20.110 --> 00:35:21.222 align:middle line:90%
[INAUDIBLE]

00:35:21.222 --> 00:35:23.582 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHING]

00:35:23.582 --> 00:35:27.141 align:middle line:90%


00:35:27.141 --> 00:35:29.720 align:middle line:84%
-OK.
-Are you still into this stuff?

00:35:29.720 --> 00:35:31.920 align:middle line:84%
-As if you aren't?
-Whatever.

00:35:31.920 --> 00:35:34.390 align:middle line:84%
I read "Conversations with
God" like everyone else.

00:35:34.390 --> 00:35:35.370 align:middle line:90%
You read more than that.

00:35:35.370 --> 00:35:37.216 align:middle line:90%
You read more than I did.

00:35:37.216 --> 00:35:38.615 align:middle line:84%
FREDRICK: Are you
seeing anyone right now?

00:35:38.615 --> 00:35:41.035 align:middle line:84%
That came out of nowhere.
FREDRICK: Sorry.

00:35:41.035 --> 00:35:43.800 align:middle line:90%
It just crossed my mind.

00:35:43.800 --> 00:35:45.430 align:middle line:90%
Are you?

00:35:45.430 --> 00:35:46.690 align:middle line:90%
Not really.

00:35:46.690 --> 00:35:48.470 align:middle line:90%
I've become much choosier.

00:35:48.470 --> 00:35:50.290 align:middle line:84%
Is that supposed to
make me feel good.

00:35:50.290 --> 00:35:51.640 align:middle line:90%
Before, I was picky.

00:35:51.640 --> 00:35:53.220 align:middle line:90%
Now, it's worse.

00:35:53.220 --> 00:35:55.490 align:middle line:84%
-What changed?
-I guess I did.

00:35:55.490 --> 00:35:57.550 align:middle line:90%
I know what I want now.

00:35:57.550 --> 00:35:58.940 align:middle line:90%
So it took me to get you there.

00:35:58.940 --> 00:36:01.660 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: You, and a whole
lot of other experiences.

00:36:01.660 --> 00:36:04.630 align:middle line:84%
No man that sparks that
fire breathing soul of yours?

00:36:04.630 --> 00:36:06.060 align:middle line:84%
You were never short
of opportunities.

00:36:06.060 --> 00:36:07.050 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:36:07.050 --> 00:36:08.620 align:middle line:84%
It's like me not being
able to imagine you

00:36:08.620 --> 00:36:11.440 align:middle line:90%
settling down with one woman.

00:36:11.440 --> 00:36:13.121 align:middle line:90%
Are you serious?

00:36:13.121 --> 00:36:14.420 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: That was
the thing with you.

00:36:14.420 --> 00:36:16.430 align:middle line:84%
Even when you were with
me, you weren't with me.

00:36:16.430 --> 00:36:17.970 align:middle line:84%
That's what I was trying
to tell you before.

00:36:17.970 --> 00:36:18.390 align:middle line:90%
How can you that?

00:36:18.390 --> 00:36:20.280 align:middle line:84%
You always used to say
that, and it was never true.

00:36:20.280 --> 00:36:21.410 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't matter if
it was true or not.

00:36:21.410 --> 00:36:22.610 align:middle line:84%
It's what I was
feeling at the time.

00:36:22.610 --> 00:36:24.400 align:middle line:84%
Whether it was true for
you is not the point.

00:36:24.400 --> 00:36:26.690 align:middle line:90%
Of course it's the point.

00:36:26.690 --> 00:36:29.400 align:middle line:84%
I mean, what you're accusing
me of is not being faithful.

00:36:29.400 --> 00:36:32.740 align:middle line:84%
-Well.
-One time.

00:36:32.740 --> 00:36:34.680 align:middle line:84%
And I know that one
time is unacceptable.

00:36:34.680 --> 00:36:38.030 align:middle line:84%
But just like you've
been asking to understand

00:36:38.030 --> 00:36:39.616 align:middle line:84%
how you're feeling, I
need you to understand.

00:36:39.616 --> 00:36:41.730 align:middle line:90%
Understand what?

00:36:41.730 --> 00:36:45.080 align:middle line:84%
To this day, I still don't
understand what happened.

00:36:45.080 --> 00:36:47.510 align:middle line:84%
I was so in love
with you, and yet, I

00:36:47.510 --> 00:36:49.490 align:middle line:90%
almost threw it all away.

00:36:49.490 --> 00:36:52.440 align:middle line:84%
I've never been so disgusted
with myself in my life.

00:36:52.440 --> 00:36:55.641 align:middle line:90%
Then why did you do it?

00:36:55.641 --> 00:36:57.340 align:middle line:84%
I guess I tried to prove
that I didn't deserve it,

00:36:57.340 --> 00:37:01.710 align:middle line:90%
which is what I really felt.

00:37:01.710 --> 00:37:03.062 align:middle line:84%
Oh, well, at least
now you understand.

00:37:03.062 --> 00:37:03.995 align:middle line:90%
I just hope you understand.

00:37:03.995 --> 00:37:05.290 align:middle line:90%
I understood back then.

00:37:05.290 --> 00:37:07.641 align:middle line:90%
Why do you think I forgave you?

00:37:07.641 --> 00:37:08.540 align:middle line:90%
Did you really forgive me?

00:37:08.540 --> 00:37:10.140 align:middle line:84%
Or was it just some
temporary lapse?

00:37:10.140 --> 00:37:11.561 align:middle line:90%
What are you talking about?

00:37:11.561 --> 00:37:14.330 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:37:14.330 --> 00:37:16.640 align:middle line:84%
Maybe I just can't
imagine being forgiven.

00:37:16.640 --> 00:37:18.990 align:middle line:84%
I think that's
exactly what it is.

00:37:18.990 --> 00:37:22.050 align:middle line:84%
That's why it never
healed inside of you.

00:37:22.050 --> 00:37:23.826 align:middle line:90%
Have you ever read this book?

00:37:23.826 --> 00:37:25.680 align:middle line:84%
FREDRICK: "The Dark Side
of the Light Chasers."

00:37:25.680 --> 00:37:26.690 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:37:26.690 --> 00:37:28.380 align:middle line:90%
It's about shadow work.

00:37:28.380 --> 00:37:29.710 align:middle line:84%
See, we all have
these shadow parts

00:37:29.710 --> 00:37:31.980 align:middle line:84%
of ourselves that influence
nearly everything we do.

00:37:31.980 --> 00:37:34.490 align:middle line:84%
And most of the time, we try to
hide them or get rid of them,

00:37:34.490 --> 00:37:36.700 align:middle line:84%
and that just makes
them stronger.

00:37:36.700 --> 00:37:40.880 align:middle line:84%
This book is about embracing
them and integrating them

00:37:40.880 --> 00:37:43.110 align:middle line:90%
into our lives.

00:37:43.110 --> 00:37:44.410 align:middle line:84%
Have you done that?
KATHERINE: Shadow work?

00:37:44.410 --> 00:37:46.950 align:middle line:84%
Yeah.
It's brutal, but it works.

00:37:46.950 --> 00:37:48.290 align:middle line:90%
So what was your shadow?

00:37:48.290 --> 00:37:50.720 align:middle line:84%
First of all, it's none
of your damn business.

00:37:50.720 --> 00:37:53.730 align:middle line:84%
And secondly, we all
have tons of them.

00:37:53.730 --> 00:37:56.120 align:middle line:84%
For example, if I were
afraid of commitment,

00:37:56.120 --> 00:38:00.650 align:middle line:84%
I would face that part, name
it, and make friends with it.

00:38:00.650 --> 00:38:04.640 align:middle line:84%
Maybe I would name her
Uncommitted Connie.

00:38:04.640 --> 00:38:05.680 align:middle line:90%
Oh my god.

00:38:05.680 --> 00:38:06.380 align:middle line:90%
KATHERINE: What?

00:38:06.380 --> 00:38:09.980 align:middle line:90%


00:38:09.980 --> 00:38:12.200 align:middle line:90%
It's silly.

00:38:12.200 --> 00:38:15.490 align:middle line:84%
Well, if I were
cheap, maybe I would

00:38:15.490 --> 00:38:17.780 align:middle line:90%
name that part Charlie Cheapo.

00:38:17.780 --> 00:38:20.610 align:middle line:90%
You talking to me?

00:38:20.610 --> 00:38:21.670 align:middle line:90%
You were always cheap.

00:38:21.670 --> 00:38:24.340 align:middle line:84%
You just pushed it aside so you
didn't have to deal with it?

00:38:24.340 --> 00:38:25.920 align:middle line:84%
And you're like
Ridiculous Rita.

00:38:25.920 --> 00:38:27.670 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: Well,
you're Denying Dennis.

00:38:27.670 --> 00:38:30.500 align:middle line:84%
Can we go back to being
just Fredrick and Catherine?

00:38:30.500 --> 00:38:32.240 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:38:32.240 --> 00:38:33.390 align:middle line:90%
Fredrick the frady-cat.

00:38:33.390 --> 00:38:37.220 align:middle line:90%


00:38:37.220 --> 00:38:38.570 align:middle line:84%
It sort of reminds
me of couples

00:38:38.570 --> 00:38:40.050 align:middle line:84%
that always have
these cute little

00:38:40.050 --> 00:38:42.470 align:middle line:90%
pet names they give each other.

00:38:42.470 --> 00:38:45.680 align:middle line:84%
But what happens to those
names when they split apart?

00:38:45.680 --> 00:38:46.810 align:middle line:90%
Do they just dissolve?

00:38:46.810 --> 00:38:51.020 align:middle line:84%
Or are they like windows into
worlds we think we forgot?

00:38:51.020 --> 00:38:51.820 align:middle line:90%
I mean, let's face it.

00:38:51.820 --> 00:38:54.140 align:middle line:84%
There's some things
we never forget.

00:38:54.140 --> 00:38:58.730 align:middle line:10%
Unless, of course,
you're Forgetful Frank.

00:38:58.730 --> 00:39:01.300 align:middle line:84%
FREDRICK: Do you think
magnets change with time?

00:39:01.300 --> 00:39:02.490 align:middle line:90%
What are you talking about?

00:39:02.490 --> 00:39:07.707 align:middle line:84%
If you buried a magnet for six
years, would it lose its field?

00:39:07.707 --> 00:39:09.740 align:middle line:84%
If you put it next to another
magnet, would it still attract?

00:39:09.740 --> 00:39:12.677 align:middle line:84%
I think this has more to do
with you and I than magnets.

00:39:12.677 --> 00:39:14.010 align:middle line:84%
Time doesn't seem
to have changed much.

00:39:14.010 --> 00:39:14.890 align:middle line:90%
Time doesn't change.

00:39:14.890 --> 00:39:16.110 align:middle line:90%
It just waffles.

00:39:16.110 --> 00:39:16.850 align:middle line:90%
Waffles?

00:39:16.850 --> 00:39:20.360 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, like someone who
can't make up their mind.

00:39:20.360 --> 00:39:22.350 align:middle line:84%
Haven't you ever noticed
that one five year

00:39:22.350 --> 00:39:24.320 align:middle line:84%
period may age you 10
years, while another

00:39:24.320 --> 00:39:26.890 align:middle line:90%
gives you five back?

00:39:26.890 --> 00:39:28.570 align:middle line:84%
Haven't you ever
seen two brothers

00:39:28.570 --> 00:39:31.200 align:middle line:84%
who are about the same age but
live totally different lives?

00:39:31.200 --> 00:39:33.940 align:middle line:84%
One feels totally
worn down by life,

00:39:33.940 --> 00:39:35.590 align:middle line:84%
and the other doesn't seem
to be affected at all.

00:39:35.590 --> 00:39:37.310 align:middle line:84%
-You're losing me.
-OK.

00:39:37.310 --> 00:39:38.510 align:middle line:84%
There are these two
brothers, right?

00:39:38.510 --> 00:39:39.220 align:middle line:90%
Little boys.

00:39:39.220 --> 00:39:41.226 align:middle line:84%
And one is a total
optimist, while the other

00:39:41.226 --> 00:39:42.770 align:middle line:90%
is a total pessimist.

00:39:42.770 --> 00:39:46.180 align:middle line:84%
So one day, the parents decide
to even them out a little bit.

00:39:46.180 --> 00:39:49.210 align:middle line:84%
And for Christmas, they decide
to get the pessimist boy

00:39:49.210 --> 00:39:50.670 align:middle line:90%
everything he could want.

00:39:50.670 --> 00:39:51.915 align:middle line:84%
While to the
optimistic, they give

00:39:51.915 --> 00:39:54.484 align:middle line:90%
a big box full of horse manure.

00:39:54.484 --> 00:39:55.750 align:middle line:84%
What kind of messed
up story is this?

00:39:55.750 --> 00:39:56.790 align:middle line:90%
Don't interrupt.

00:39:56.790 --> 00:40:00.600 align:middle line:84%
So then, Christmas Day comes,
and the pessimist boy opens up

00:40:00.600 --> 00:40:02.350 align:middle line:84%
his presents to see that
Santa Claus has given

00:40:02.350 --> 00:40:03.870 align:middle line:90%
him everything he could want.

00:40:03.870 --> 00:40:05.420 align:middle line:90%
And he's totally dissatisfied.

00:40:05.420 --> 00:40:07.480 align:middle line:84%
He's like, this
train won't work.

00:40:07.480 --> 00:40:08.860 align:middle line:90%
This truck's gonna brake.

00:40:08.860 --> 00:40:10.460 align:middle line:84%
I can't wait to hear
what the other kid though.

00:40:10.460 --> 00:40:14.270 align:middle line:84%
So the optimist boy opens up
his presents to see that he has

00:40:14.270 --> 00:40:16.530 align:middle line:90%
a big box full of horse manure.

00:40:16.530 --> 00:40:20.000 align:middle line:84%
And his parents look to see
how he's going to react.

00:40:20.000 --> 00:40:23.060 align:middle line:84%
Well, he starts
digging through it,

00:40:23.060 --> 00:40:25.360 align:middle line:90%
having the time of his life.

00:40:25.360 --> 00:40:27.400 align:middle line:84%
And his parents ask
him what he's doing.

00:40:27.400 --> 00:40:31.310 align:middle line:84%
And he says, well, I
figured with all this shit,

00:40:31.310 --> 00:40:35.490 align:middle line:84%
there's bound to be a
pony in here somewhere.

00:40:35.490 --> 00:40:37.380 align:middle line:84%
I have no idea why you
just told me that story.

00:40:37.380 --> 00:40:40.980 align:middle line:84%
It shows you that everything in
life is a decision, even time.

00:40:40.980 --> 00:40:42.820 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you can have
everything you ever wanted

00:40:42.820 --> 00:40:46.930 align:middle line:84%
and be totally dissatisfied, or
have a box full of horse shit

00:40:46.930 --> 00:40:48.360 align:middle line:84%
and be the happiest
person on Earth.

00:40:48.360 --> 00:40:49.910 align:middle line:84%
So what happened
to the optimist boy

00:40:49.910 --> 00:40:52.260 align:middle line:84%
when he realized
there was no pony?

00:40:52.260 --> 00:40:54.857 align:middle line:84%
I never thought the
story through that far.

00:40:54.857 --> 00:40:55.990 align:middle line:84%
I'm trying to
remember what it is

00:40:55.990 --> 00:40:57.223 align:middle line:84%
we were talking
about before you went

00:40:57.223 --> 00:40:58.570 align:middle line:90%
off on that bizarre tangent.

00:40:58.570 --> 00:41:00.180 align:middle line:84%
That sometimes, the
things that we think

00:41:00.180 --> 00:41:02.874 align:middle line:84%
are worst are really best
for us, and vice versa.

00:41:02.874 --> 00:41:04.340 align:middle line:84%
Actually, I have to
agree with you on that,

00:41:04.340 --> 00:41:06.724 align:middle line:84%
especially in terms of what
we were just talking about.

00:41:06.724 --> 00:41:08.190 align:middle line:84%
Even though it was the
worst thing I'd done,

00:41:08.190 --> 00:41:09.900 align:middle line:90%
it changed me completely.

00:41:09.900 --> 00:41:12.000 align:middle line:84%
If I hadn't done it, I might
not be where I am today.

00:41:12.000 --> 00:41:13.900 align:middle line:90%
In a great marriage to Susan.

00:41:13.900 --> 00:41:16.801 align:middle line:84%
Well, it took me a year to
realize that we were together

00:41:16.801 --> 00:41:18.000 align:middle line:84%
for whatever the
right reasons were,

00:41:18.000 --> 00:41:21.710 align:middle line:84%
but they weren't
necessarily my reasons.

00:41:21.710 --> 00:41:23.296 align:middle line:90%
Anyway.

00:41:23.296 --> 00:41:25.195 align:middle line:84%
If that hadn't of happened,
I might never have grown up.

00:41:25.195 --> 00:41:27.200 align:middle line:90%
I wouldn't call you a grown up.

00:41:27.200 --> 00:41:28.450 align:middle line:90%
As if you are.

00:41:28.450 --> 00:41:30.060 align:middle line:90%
I'm more grown up than you.

00:41:30.060 --> 00:41:30.930 align:middle line:90%
Hm.

00:41:30.930 --> 00:41:31.841 align:middle line:90%
Please.

00:41:31.841 --> 00:41:33.740 align:middle line:84%
You're the one writing a book
about a failed relationship

00:41:33.740 --> 00:41:34.820 align:middle line:90%
that ended six years ago.

00:41:34.820 --> 00:41:36.090 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, and you're
the one who makes

00:41:36.090 --> 00:41:37.850 align:middle line:84%
a living writing stories
about the longest

00:41:37.850 --> 00:41:40.260 align:middle line:90%
string of popcorn in the world.

00:41:40.260 --> 00:41:41.840 align:middle line:90%
At least I make a living.

00:41:41.840 --> 00:41:42.820 align:middle line:90%
I make a living.

00:41:42.820 --> 00:41:44.219 align:middle line:84%
What does that mean?
I could buy a house.

00:41:44.219 --> 00:41:45.639 align:middle line:84%
Do you have a house?
I don't think so.

00:41:45.639 --> 00:41:46.990 align:middle line:90%
I bet you Susan's rich.

00:41:46.990 --> 00:41:47.690 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:41:47.690 --> 00:41:49.020 align:middle line:84%
We do own our own home.
-You do?

00:41:49.020 --> 00:41:50.100 align:middle line:84%
[INAUDIBLE].
KATHERINE: How big is it?

00:41:50.100 --> 00:41:50.740 align:middle line:90%
FREDRICK: [INAUDIBLE].

00:41:50.740 --> 00:41:51.439 align:middle line:90%
KATHERINE: Oh, right.

00:41:51.439 --> 00:42:09.330 align:middle line:90%


00:42:09.330 --> 00:42:11.130 align:middle line:84%
FREDRICK: I was watching
this movie a while back

00:42:11.130 --> 00:42:13.152 align:middle line:84%
about this couple
who meet in heaven

00:42:13.152 --> 00:42:14.290 align:middle line:84%
and decided that
they should find

00:42:14.290 --> 00:42:16.160 align:middle line:90%
a way to get together on Earth.

00:42:16.160 --> 00:42:17.074 align:middle line:90%
KATHERINE: Do they?

00:42:17.074 --> 00:42:18.240 align:middle line:84%
FREDRICK: Yeah,
but they have to go

00:42:18.240 --> 00:42:20.350 align:middle line:84%
through all this terrible
stuff before they can meet.

00:42:20.350 --> 00:42:22.490 align:middle line:84%
It's like they had
to learn whatever

00:42:22.490 --> 00:42:24.350 align:middle line:84%
it was they came
to Earth to learn

00:42:24.350 --> 00:42:25.444 align:middle line:90%
before they can get together.

00:42:25.444 --> 00:42:26.810 align:middle line:84%
KATHERINE: It's kind
of opposite with us.

00:42:26.810 --> 00:42:28.060 align:middle line:90%
How do you mean?

00:42:28.060 --> 00:42:30.320 align:middle line:84%
Well, we met back then,
went through a lot,

00:42:30.320 --> 00:42:32.914 align:middle line:90%
only to reunite now.

00:42:32.914 --> 00:42:34.470 align:middle line:84%
What would you say the
main thing that you've

00:42:34.470 --> 00:42:36.010 align:middle line:90%
learned since then would be?

00:42:36.010 --> 00:42:37.115 align:middle line:90%
The main thing?

00:42:37.115 --> 00:42:38.300 align:middle line:90%
Mmhm.

00:42:38.300 --> 00:42:40.900 align:middle line:84%
I guess it would be
that I can't expect

00:42:40.900 --> 00:42:42.350 align:middle line:90%
anyone to give me anything.

00:42:42.350 --> 00:42:44.280 align:middle line:84%
I mean, if I can't
